title: nut bread
directions: Mix a little of the flour with the nuts; mix flour with baking powder.
Beat egg; add sugar and salt.
Add milk and flour alternately, then the nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cinnamon apple punch
directions: In bottom of percolator, pour apple cider and ginger ale.
In basket of percolator, put red hot cinnamon candies, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Perk.
Makes 30 cups.

title: hunan noodle dinner
directions: Fry together the ground meat, ginger, garlic and onion.
(Meat can be cooked first and drain fat.)
Stir often to keep consistency very fine.
Add to this the mushroom sauce, sesame oil and wine.
Lower heat and stir well.

title: ann's salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and chill in refrigerator for at least two hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool chicken.
In a large saucepan, take broth, rice and onion, bring to a boil and simmer for 14 minutes.
Add soups and salad dressings.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll or pat each biscuit to a 3 1/2 to 4-inch circle; fit over backs of well-greased muffin pans.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (shortening, brown sugar and molasses).
Stir in water.
Add dry ingredients and form dough. Chill dough 1 hour. Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Combine margarine, light brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Blend flour into mixture.
Chill, covered, 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
With thumb, make indentation in center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are a delicate golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool.
Place 1/4 teaspoon jelly in center of each cookie.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sondie's coke salad
directions: Boil cherries, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add drained pineapple, nuts and Coke.
Let chill overnight.

title: see's fudge
directions: Boil sugar and condensed milk about 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow.
Whip butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into bowl.
Stir until creamy.
Add chopped nuts and pour into large pan to set.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until cooked.
Layer in bottom of a baking dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup. Top with cheese slices and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place onion rings on top and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 more minutes or until done.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat electric skillet to 375° for 2 minutes.
Add bacon drippings and heat 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir-fry about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: bread pudding with irish whiskey sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss dried fruit with flour and finely chop.
Scald milk over low heat (do not boil).
Set aside.
Whip eggs until frothy, slowly stir in sugar and whip until smooth. Add sugar and egg mixture to scalded milk.
Stir in vanilla. Place bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with fruit and raisins.
Pour milk and egg mixture over bread.
Using the back of a large spoon, press the bread down into the pan so milk mixture is absorbed.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place pan into large pan filled with 1-inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is deep golden brown.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate.
Fry the bacon until brown.
Blot off excess grease with paper towel. (Crumble.)
Sprinkle bacon, onions, cheese and peppers on bottom of plate.
Mix eggs, milk, Bisquick, pepper and salt together until smooth.
Pour the mixture into pie plate; bake 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Slowly beat in sugars. Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Stir flour with soda and oats. Stir into first mixture. Stir in peanuts and chocolate bits.
Mix well. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: chili cheese corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter 1 1/2-quart baking dish or cast-iron skillet. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well combined. Transfer to prepared dish. Bake in preheated oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Mix in shortening (cut in	well).	Mix
water
and vinegar with beaten egg.
Add egg mixture
to
flour mixture.
Add a little flour as needed, so you can
divide the dough into pieces.	Makes 2 double pie crusts. Freeze extra dough.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers and dice other ingredients in separate vessels. Mix alternately and thoroughly.
Add cream last and pack firmly in greased or wax paper lined pan or baking dish.
Chill well and slice as needed.

title: low-fat angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda two times in large bowl. Mix egg whites at high speed until foamy.
Add lemon juice, cream of tartar, vanilla, almond extract and honey.
Continue mixing until egg whites form a peak.
Mix in flour mixture.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: pizza by-the-yard
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise.
Combine tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, onion, olives, oregano, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat; mix well.
Spread over top of loaf halves.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with tomato slices and green pepper rings.
Sprinkle cheese on top of tomatoes.
Bake 5 minutes.
I cover pizza with foil on first baking so bread does not burn.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cuban-style roast pork
directions: Slit the meat in several places and push a bit of garlic into each cut.
Rub the roast with oregano and black pepper.
To be authentic, use plenty of pepper.
Place in a deep bowl.
Add juice and the shell of one fruit after juicing it.
Marinate in the refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix crushed wafers and melted margarine and press into spring-form (10-inch) pan (bottom and sides).

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and oil in saucepan to a rolling boil.
Add flour sifted with salt all at once and stir vigorously.
As soon as mixed remove from heat.
Cool and mix in unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder and mix.
Place large spoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add grits slowly and cook until done. Add salt, grated cheese, remaining ingredients and beaten eggs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. wilson's pulled mints
directions: Saturate sugar with water.
Add butter and cook without stirring until mixture reaches 260° on a candy thermometer.
Pour immediately onto a cold marble slab.
Turn edges and keep moving to cool places on slab.
Take up and start pulling as soon as possible.
Add desired flavor when taffy is about 1/8 pulled. Continue pulling until taffy is hard to pull and firm.
Stretch taffy into long rope on table top and cut immediately into desired lengths with scissors.
Put into tin boxes and store until mints turn creamy.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Bring the last 4 ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for a long time.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add other ingredients in the order they appear, starting with sugar, then flour, etc.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for one hour or until browned.

title: never soggy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt together until crumbly.
Beat egg, add water to beaten egg, beat, then add vinegar.
Add the egg-water-vinegar mixture to flour-Crisco-salt mixture.
Mix well, roll into size crust required.
Makes 3 single pie crusts.
Bake according to directions of your pie recipe.

title: hot punch
directions: Combine in percolator.
Put 1 stick cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon cloves in percolator basket.

title: holiday chicken wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except rolls. Unroll crescent rolls and arrange triangles in a circle on a large cookie sheet with bases overlapping in center and points toward the outside of the circle. Spoon filling mixture onto widest portion of each triangle. Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center (filling will not be completely covered). Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, chicken broth, celery soup and chopped onion in casserole dish.
Cut up margarine on top.
Mix milk and flour and pour on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine the first

5 ingredients in mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer for 1 minute. Combine remaining ingredients, except nuts, and add to applesauce mixture, beating until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spoon into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Allow to cool in pan on rack for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and continue to cool on rack.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Place spaghetti in pan.
Brown, salt and drain ground beef.
Mix together milk and eggs.
Pour over spaghetti in pan.
Cover spaghetti with grated Cheddar cheese.
Place drained ground beef over cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over meat.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take the frozen dough out the night before and cover with a thin coat of oil or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and let it rise overnight.
Next day, knead dough and roll out to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Don't forget to flour your surface!
Cook broccoli and season to your taste (I use garlic salt), then on top of your dough, put the cheese and then cooked broccoli and roll up!
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and kraut
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Put sauerkraut, pepper, salt and Russian dressing on top.
Top with cheese and mix in.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour until brown on top.
Serves 4.

title: quick and easy supper
directions: Brown hamburger in microwave; drain and add barbecue sauce. Cook macaroni by directions on box.
Layer hamburger mixture and macaroni in another bowl and heat 5 minutes in microwave.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Pick over nutmeats.
Melt the chocolate pieces with shortening in top of double boiler over hot water (not boiling).
Pour in 1/2 cup nuts (one kind at a time).
Stir around in the melted chocolate.
Take out nuts with fork and place little piles on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until set.

title: stuffed ham celery
directions: Cut celery in 3-inch pieces.
Combine cream cheese and ham, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Spread on celery.

title: orange tapioca jello
directions: Combine water, pudding and jello; bring to a boil and cook 1 minute. Let cool 2 hours to room temperature. Add Cool Whip and fold in mandarin oranges. Save some out to garnish on top of salad.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large kettle, cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion, potatoes, celery, carrots, green pepper and garlic.
Pour in water and add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed with 5 cups of milk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Then layer pudding alternating with cookies, bananas and pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Combine chicken, bread crumbs, onion and eggs in medium bowl and blend well.
Season with salt and pepper, cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Form chicken mixture into 6 patties.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add patties and fry until browned, turning once.
Serve on buns with tomatoes, lettuce, onion, mayonnaise, mustard, etc.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the oil in a bowl.
Heat the oil in a cast-iron skillet over medium heat.
Pour the batter into the skillet, reducing the heat to low.
Let cook for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.
Place a plate over the skillet and turn the skillet over to release the bread.
Return the bread to the skillet to cook the other side over low heat for 15 minutes more until well browned.
Or, the bread can be baked for about 35 minutes in the oven at 375° instead.
Cut in wedges to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and butter together.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 6.
Serve plain or with syrup or cream.

title: oatmeal breakfast bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter; pour into small bowl.
Mix flour, oats, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda into a large bowl.
Add sugar and egg to the butter, whisk smooth.
Stir in raisins.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Drop heaping tablespoonful of batter onto cookie sheet, leaving 2 inches between each (cookies spread).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until cookies are lightly brown.

title: fresh veggie spread
directions: Grate vegetables and drain dry.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill 2 or more hours.
Spread on crackers or party breads.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Use recipe on cake package.
Just before turning batter into pan, fold semi-sweet chocolate pieces into batter.
After baking, according to cake directions, frost.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg, melted Crisco, orange juice and hot water.
Mix only until blended.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until done).

title: fish rolls
directions: Remove small bone of fish by cutting in half.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and chives.
Cut Swiss cheese in strips.
Put several strips in fish slice and roll up.
Repeat for each fish piece. Cover top of fish with salt, pepper, paprika and butter.
Broil until golden brown.
Dot with sour cream, parsley and butter just before completely done.

title: cheesy sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool, peel and shred.
Chop 1 onion.
Melt oleo and add onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add shredded potatoes, cheese, sour cream, onion and oleo.
Mix together.
Put in an ovenproof dish.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Substitute 1 1/2 cups coleslaw for sauerkraut.
Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Spread over 6 slices of bread.
Arrange cheese, corned beef and sauerkraut on top of mayonnaise mixture.
Top with remaining bread slices (if desired, spread margarine over both sides of each sandwich).
Cook over low heat until bottom is golden brown and cheese begins to melt, about 10 minutes.
Turn and cook other side the same.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain.
In separate skillet cook pepperoni until sides curl.
Drain.
Add pepperoni to ground beef.
Stir in the spaghetti sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and onion and simmer 20 minutes.
Bring 2 quarts water to boil and add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Drain.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt, buttermilk and vanilla until well mixed.
Gently stir in drained fruits.
Pour into dish and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: red pineapple punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir and serve with ice.
A real favorite with mom and kids.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: beer pastry
directions: Put the shortening in a bowl and cream it by hand until creamy. Add salt, baking powder and sugar; continue beating, adding the flour little by little.

Continue by adding the beer until you have a soft dough. Knead. You will have 1 large ball. Divide it into small balls and flatten them like tortillas. Put marmalade or jelly in the center and fold in the middle. Seal the edges by pressing them with a fork. Put them on a greased cookie sheet and cook them in a 400° oven until brown. Roll them in powdered sugar.

title: butter sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together baking mix and water to form a soft dough.
Shape dough into a ball on a floured surface and knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 10 x 6-inch rectangle.
Cut lengthwise into strips about 3/4-inch wide and cut strips into pieces about 3 inches each.
Dip each "stick" into the melted butter, making sure both sides are coated.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 24 sticks.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Roll into balls and brown. (I brown in microwave in bowl with a "drip pan" in top.) Place in baking dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries and orange through food chopper and let drain. Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cool water. Add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in oiled shallow dish until firm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and add fruit cocktail, including liquid.
Fold into flour mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Top with 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Place all above in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cake mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Prick cake with fork.
Spoon icing over cake.

title: pepper pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir in pecans. Let stand for 30 minutes and drain.
Spread pecans in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
(Pecans can be stored up to 2 weeks in an airtight container.)

title: chicken salad appetizers
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients (except pea pods); mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors. Spoon or pipe one teaspoonful of filling into each pea pod or pipe one teaspoonful of filling onto cucumber slice.
Yields 2 to 2 1/2 dozen appetizers.

title: piccalilli
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and peppers through food chopper and drain and discard liquid.
Place vegetables in large kettle; add 1 qt. vinegar and boil 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain and discard liquid.
Return vegetables to kettle and add remaining pt. of vinegar, sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon; celery seeds and mustard seeds.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Immediately ladle into 6 hot pint jars.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Count time after water starts to boil.

title: brown derby burgers
directions: Mix ingredients, adding broth last to give the mixture the consistency of soupy meat loaf.
Using 1 cup of mixture for each portion, make thick patties and brown them in fat.
Then follow directions for Sauce Diablo.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread mixture over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch (or larger) dish.
Spread the beans over the mixture, then the lettuce, salsa and cheese.
Prepare at least 2 hours ahead or mix the cheese and taco seasoning together and spread in the dish the day before.
It's better to let the seasonings blend.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients, do not add popcorn yet.
Bring to rolling
boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add popped popcorn and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Very Hot!
Let cool and store in plastic bags or in waxed paper.

title: yeast coffee cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add balance of ingredients and mix slightly.
Add flour until dough is not sticky and can be turned out on counter to knead (about 5 cups). Knead until it holds its shape.
Put in greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down. Let rise 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Knead 1/2 gently stretching it as you go.
Roll out lengthwise and across until a rectangle is formed.
Spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion (form circle), tucking in ends.
Slice almost through at 1-inch intervals.
Turn slices sideways.
Cover.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk orange jello
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add jello and stir until jello dissolves.
Let cool completely.
Then add buttermilk and cool whip.
Let set.
Can be molded.

title: punch
directions: Put jello, sugar and hot water into gallon container; mix until sugar and jello are dissolved. Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemonade. Shake well. Freeze overnight.
When ready to serve, put into punch bowl. Add ginger ale.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Cook the meat, pepper and onion in skillet slow, not brown. Drain off grease.
Add the rest.
Add water as needed.
Simmer at low heat for 1 hour.
(This is good served with spaghetti.)

title: club sandwich
directions: Spread toast with butter.
Top first slice with lettuce and chicken or turkey.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Top with second toast slice.
Add tomato and bacon.
Top with third toast slice.
Anchor with 4 wooden picks.
Cut diagonally in quarters.
Makes 1.

title: kentucky chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pecans in pastry shell; set aside.
Combine chocolate and butter in medium saucepan; cook over low heat until melted, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture over pecans. Bake for 1 hour or until knife inserted one inch from edge comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream butter.
Add sugar substitute, vanilla and egg, blending well.
Add flour mixture. Beat well.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Each cookie is 48 calories.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, oil and powdered sugar.
Add eggs, flavoring, cream of tartar, soda, salt and flour.
Mix all well.
Form into balls size of walnut.
Press flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges.

title: sauce for broccoli
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then slowly add the evaporated milk. Heat over low fire until thickened and serve hot.
May also be used over asparagus.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into 1 tablespoon balls. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: english butter cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in egg yolk.
Knead in sifted flour.
Grease small cookie sheet.
Press mixture out to 1/2-inch thick.
Beat egg white and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until light brown.
Cut in squares or diamonds.

title: sweet spring salad(no sugar)
directions: In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, radishes, cucumbers and onions. In a small bowl, whisk together vinegar, water, sugar substitute, salt and pepper until sugar substitute is dissolved. Pour over vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Serve with slotted spoon.

title: curried cheese pate with chutney
directions: Line a 7 x 6-inch, 1 1/2-quart dish with waxed paper.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, curry powder, salt and sherry.
With electric mixer or food processor at medium speed, beat until smooth.
Turn into prepared dish; refrigerate, covered, until firm, 4 hours or overnight.

title: tex-mex tortilla bake
directions: Mix in a saucepan the celery, onion, green chili peppers, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, oregano and salt and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes to thicken (or until most of the moisture has burned off). Add taco mix and beef and take off the burner.
Cut 12 tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Butter the bottom of pie pan or any cake pan. Layer the bottom with tortillas, then the meat mixture and then the cheese and continue the layering effect until everything is used up.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a 4-quart pan, cook fish in enough water to cover.
When fish flakes, remove with a slotted spoon.
Measure cooking liquid, add enough to make 4 cups.
In the liquid, cook celery, onion and potatoes until tender.
Make a paste with flour and cold water. Blend into chowder.
Cook until boiling.
Add reserved fish, clams with liquid, shrimp, crab, salt, pepper, butter, milk and pimento. Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sweet plantain pie
directions: Cook meat to your taste. Boil plantains and add salt.
Mush up the plantains and add butter.
In a pan, spread the mashed plantain.
Add a layer of ground meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes, slice in half lengthwise and scoop out most of the potato, leaving the skin and about 1/4-inch of potato.
Drop potato halves into hot oil and fry until brown; then drain.
Cook bacon until crispy and break into pieces.
Top fried potato halves with cheese and bacon.
Add chopped green onions, if desired. Place under broiler in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato soup and green beans; season to taste.
Stir all together and simmer a few minutes.
Top with leftover mashed potatoes and grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: indian shrimp curry
directions: Cook rice as label directs.
Keep hot.
Melt butter in skillet. Stir in flour, curry powder, salt, sugar and ginger.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring until thickened.
Add shrimp and lemon juice.
Heat to boil carefully.
Serve ring of hot rice on heated platter.
Dice tomatoes.
Cut avocados into halves, nestle in center of rice.
Spoon curry mixture on top, then tomatoes.

title: stir-fried pork with lemon-garlic sauce
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the pork strips and stir-fry until starting to brown. Add the salt, pepper, and garlic. Continue to stir-fry until lightly browned and done, about 5 minutes. Add the lemon juice and cook another minute. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve immediately.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Make crumbs from bread in blender or
processor.
Mix
cheese,
crumbs
and spinach.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; add half and half and seasonings. Pour over
spinach mixture in a buttered 1 1/2-quart ovenproof dish.
Let stand
hour.

Bake

and serve hot. Recipe can be doubled.
This may be frozen after baking.
Thaw and reheat 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup cream of coconut, 1/2 cup rum, oil and eggs. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-in tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
With a tableknife or skewer, poke holes about 1 inch apart in cake, almost to bottom.
Combine remaining cream of coconut and rum.
Pour over cake.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour and salt; mix well. Coat the bottom of a mixing bowl with oil.
Place mixed dough in bowl and cover to let rest for 20 minutes.
Remove dough; knead for 3 minutes, adding flour if it is sticky.
Roll out to desired size.
Put into pan.
Add pizza sauce and your favorite toppings. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put in foil and seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Slice zucchini in a large skillet.
Cook zucchini and onion in hot oil for 2 minutes or until just crisp.
Do not overcook.
Add cut-up undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce and oregano.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve hot or cold with crackers.

title: prune cake
directions: Into large bowl of electric mixer, put flour, sugar, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, salad oil, eggs, jar of prunes and nuts.
Beat on medium speed just until well blended.
Do
not overmix.
Turn into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lightly floured. Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
You may glaze or ice this cake, if desired.

title: sinner's mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; drain, add other ingredients and mash.

title: parmesan topped stuffed potato
directions: In small nonstick skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add shallots (or onion) and saute briefly, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Scoop pulp from potato halves into small bowl, reserving shells; add sauteed shallots (or onion), broccoli, yogurt, salt and pepper; mash until thoroughly blended.
Divide mixture into reserved shells and sprinkle each with one teaspoon cheese.
Bake until lightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: man's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except catsup.
Shape into loaf and brush catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon juices over top when serving.
Serves 8.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas, then roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a lightly oiled 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Heat milk; pour over bread. Let stand until completely cooled.
Cream margarine with sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add to bread mixture.
Mix well. Stir in raisins.
Pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix dry jello with sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over meat in Pyrex or Corning Ware tray.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 6 hours to 2 days.

title: fettuccine with shrimp sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken broth, wine, marjoram and dash of pepper. Bring to boiling. Add shrimp.
Return mixture to boiling. Cook 1 minute or until shrimp are tender.
Remove shrimp. Cover and set aside. Bring broth mixture to a full boil. Boil about 20 minutes or until reduced to 1/2 cup. Combine cornstarch and milk. Add to reduced mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Add cheese and chives. Stir until cheese is melted.
Return shrimp to saucepan. Heat through.
Serve with pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pier 4 cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: mexican luncheon dish
directions: Brown beef, green pepper and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on high until steaming.
Turn burner to low or warm and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toss together in
large bowl.
Cover with the following dressing.

title: lemonade pound cake
directions: Put cake mix, sour cream, lemonade mix, cream cheese and eggs in large bowl. Beat on low about 1 minute to mix. Increase speed to medium and beat about 2 minutes more.

title: cracker treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break crackers into sections.
Put a layer of foil in bottom of cookie sheet.
Spread crackers in pan. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Put butter, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Heat on low to boiling.
Boil 7 minutes.
Quickly stir in vanilla and drizzle over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute in pan, then put on wax paper to cool completely.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix; roll in ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
While hot, press Hershey's Kiss into center of cookie.

title: frosty orange drink
directions: Put all ingredients into a liquid blender. Blend until smooth.

title: pecan pie #4
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add corn syrup; beat eggs until light. Add butter and cream; add salt and vanilla. Fold in nut meats. Bake in uncooked pie shell in 325° oven.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Just stir until mixed.
Fry like pancakes.
Serve with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: orange filling
directions: Place honey in a small saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup orange juice in a jar with a lid and shake until smooth. Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Stir in cinnamon and butter.
Cook until butter melts.
Cool before using.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: spankopita
directions: Drain spinach well.
Mix spinach with both cheeses.
Melt butter completely.
Carefully roll out phyllo dough into buttered 11 x 13-inch pan.
Butter up the phyllo.
Spread cheese and spinach mix over phyllo.
Butter that and then cover with remaining phyllo.
Butter top generously.

title: nippy nuggets
directions: Cut brisket into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in hot oil.
Add carrots, onion, tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, water and salt.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to beef mixture and stir until thick and bubbly.
Prepare curly noodles according to package instructions. Serve beef mixture over noodles.
Garnish with carrot curls and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, pour in plastic flower pot.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Crush 1/2 pound Oreos in food processor and pour over top of mixture.
Place artificial flowers in center. Use gummy worms to decorate.
Use as centerpiece for table.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Blend in Cool Whip, then sour cream. In dish, layer bananas, then vanilla wafers.
Pour mixture of pudding, Cool Whip and sour cream over these layers.
(Repeat.) Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: quicky cheese sauce
directions: In the top of double boiler, melt cheese.
While stirring, add milk and pepper.
Great over all vegetables.

title: crock-pot beef brisket with barbecue sauce
directions: For cooking liquid, in a bowl combine first eight ingredients. Reserve 1/2 cup liquid for sauce.
Trim fat from brisket and place in 4-quart crock-pot.
Pour remaining liquid over brisket. Cover; cook on low heat setting for 10 to 12 hours or on high heat setting for 5 to 6 hours.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together 3 times the flour and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Press dough into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until pale gold (about 45 minutes).
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven and cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.
It is preferable to mix this recipe by hand.

title: rich chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt Hershey bar in chocolate syrup.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to chocolate mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Toss with potatoes. Spread into greased dish or pan.
Top with crumbs or crackers and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with a fork until the mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and stir from bottom.
Put dough on floured dough board and knead unto a soft, workable dough.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in a lightly greased pan, sides touching.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: miracle whip salad dressing cake
directions: Cream together salad dressing, sugar and cocoa.
Add flour, soda and salt, sifted together.
Add vanilla and lukewarm water last.
Grease and flour pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: all in one dinner
directions: Brown meats together and drain.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion, sage and water.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with second shell and cut several small slits in center to let steam escape.
Bake at 400° until pie crusts are brown, about 45 minutes.

title: macadamia-orange fudge
directions: With foil, line 8-inch square pan. In glass bowl, melt on High for 1 minute.
Stir in sugar and milk.
Cook on High for 8 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows and chocolate.
Stir and reheat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and liqueur or extract.
Pour into pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: norma macaroni "hot dish"
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup; place in pan.
Set in hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Heat mushroom soup in small saucepan.
Cut macaroni into 2-inch squares.
Pour undiluted soup over macaroni.
Serve.

title: aunt doris mueck's beans, beans, beans(good on cold winter days)
directions: Brown bacon; remove from skillet.
Pour off some of the grease and brown ground beef and onions; drain grease off.
Add brown sugar, granulated sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, molasses, mustard, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well.
Add 3 cans of beans. Mix lightly.
Can be baked at 350° for 1 hour or cook in slow cooker or in crock-pot for 1 hour.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, wheat germ, scallions, parsley and almonds. Set aside.
Mix together yogurt, dill, mustard and salt.
Pour yogurt mixture over cabbage mixture; toss to mix.
Pack into a 1-quart mold and refrigerate.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with carrot curls and black olives.

title: lemon chicken with vegetables
directions: Coat chicken in flour. Melt butter in skillet.
Cook chicken with garlic 5 minutes on each side until brown.
Remove chicken. Stir in broth, lemon peel, lemon juice and thyme.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add carrots; cook until crisp-tender.
Add chicken and zucchini.
Spoon juice over this.
Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Add cornmeal gradually to boiling water and let stand for a few minutes.
Add butter, salt and yolks; add buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meat; marinate overnight.

title: louisiana style baked shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in a baking dish.
In a small saucepan combine butter, powders, black pepper, cayenne pepper, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, wine and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil. Pour over shrimp.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butter pecan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish in oven.
Stir in the brown sugar, water and pecans.
Separate each can of crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press the perforation to seal.
Spread with 3 tablespoons softened butter. Combine cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over the butter.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 2-inch cubes.
Place in a pot with enough salted water to cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain well and set aside.
Chop the bacon into small pieces and saute in a medium skillet until about half done.
Add the onions and continue to cook until onions and bacon are lightly browned.
Remove from heat. Place the cooked eggplant in a bowl, then add the bacon and onions, being sure to scrape all drippings into the mixture.
Crush the saltines into small pieces and add to the eggplant mixture.
Stir thoroughly, adding egg, milk and seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.
If mixture appears too stiff, add more evaporated milk. Spoon mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 400° oven until bubbly (15 to 20 minutes).
Let sit a minute or two before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma b's oatmeal cookies(low-cal, diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray baking pan, 9 x 13-inch, with vegetable spray.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in molasses, egg substitute and orange juice concentrate.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut into bars 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
One serving equals 1 bar. Yields 32 servings.

title: wet coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake
mix as per package directions.
Bake in a sheet pan.
While
hot, punch holes into cake and pour coconut cream and Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle frozen coconut on top.
Chill.

title: bill hall's real sho-nuf stomp-down southern egg nog!
directions: Simmer ingredients (except fruit slices) together in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot with orange or lemon slice and a cinnamon stick garnish.

title: max's midnight snack
directions: Place yogurt in bowl and serve with spoon.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: In bowl combine cake mix, eggs, pumpkin, water, oil, pudding mix and cinnamon.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove to wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese icing or serve with whipped cream.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour over top. Cool and serve.

title: 24 hour omelette
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over bread cubes.
Top with layer of green onions and mushrooms.
Beat eggs, milk and spices together and pour over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour, uncover to brown, about 5 minutes.
Super brunch dish.

title: warm bacon potato salad
directions: Fry about 6 to 7 strips of bacon crisp.
Drain and crumble. Set aside.
Peel and cube potatoes (large cubes) and boil until tender (with salt).
Drain and crumble bacon and onion to taste. Mix with mayonnaise as you would for any potato salad.
Season with quite a lot of salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients while potatoes are still hot and serve warm.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Heat oleo, cocoa and water, but do not boil.
Add this to flour mixture.
Mix soda and buttermilk and add to other mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: boat dip
directions: Spread beans into bottom of flat casserole dish.
Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Put into dish.
Next, add sour cream and finally, spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: celery balls
directions: Mix well.
Form balls small.
Roll in finely chopped parsley.

title: buffet bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet, crumble and set aside.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from skillet.
Add packed brown sugar, vinegar, salt and prepared mustard.

Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. In a large bowl, combine drained butter beans, French green beans, pork and beans, lima beans, yellow wax beans, kidney beans, 1/2 can of French fried onions and hot sugar mixture.
Spoon in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with bacon and rest of onion.
Bake 5 minutes more to brown.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Heat, stirring until simmering.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Dip chicken in sauce; arrange in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Cover; bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes longer.
Do not disturb during baking.

title: winter warming fish chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, saute pepper, onion, celery and garlic in water, wine or Pam over medium heat until vegetables are crisp-tender (3 minutes).
Add undrained tomatoes, water, lemon juice, bouillon and seasonings.
Break up tomatoes with a spoon.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add noodles and fish.
Cook, covered, 7 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork and noodles are tender.
Makes 6 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix beef, milk, bread crumbs and garlic powder.
Mold into 9-inch pie tin.
Cover with tomato paste, then mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese, oregano and Parmesan.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mary's famous pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese together; add sugar, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flavorings.
Then add flour, little at a time.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Check with toothpick.

title: tomato-dill soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add celery and onion. Cook and stir 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in water, broth, tomatoes, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon dill. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, pecans, pineapple, coconut and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in unsalted water until just tender; drain. Saute onion until transparent.
Add soup to onion.
Blend into a sauce.
In baking dish layer broccoli, cheese and sauce, ending with layer of cheese.
Add onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian sausage lasagna rolls
directions: Brown crumbled sausage; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup sauce and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Put approximately 1/3 cup sausage mixture in middle of each noodle.
Fold the ends of each noodle over the mixture in center.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over noodles.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place chicken breast between wax paper.
Beat until flat. Brush each side with melted margarine; salt and pepper.
Brown quickly on each side.
Remove from pan.
Then brush each side with mustard.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Broil in pan 30 to 40 minutes on each side.

title: mushroom sauce for steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for mushrooms.
Simmer until thickened.
Add mushrooms.

title: lone star pasta salad
directions: Cook
pasta
according
to
package
directions; drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine
cooled pasta with remaining ingredients;
toss lightly until
evenly coated.
Cover; chill thoroughly before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: **pfeffernuesse(peppernuts)
directions: Beat egg whites and yolks separately, then together.
Combine ingredients as in other cakes.
Drop by teaspoons on greased tins. Bakes about 9 minutes.

title: coconut chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and lemonade, diluted according to directions.
Add ginger ale.

title: crab balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoonful in hot deep fat and fry until brown on one side and turn over and brown.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Put roast in crockpot on low overnight or until tender. Remove fat and grease. Shred roast with fork. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl to make barbecue sauce. Pour over roast. Continue cooking on low in crockpot for 4 or 5 hours or until heated through. Spoon onto buns and top with more barbecue sauce if desired.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Heat to boil the sugar and Karo.
Boil it for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter.
Stir until smooth. Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoons on buttered cookie sheets or waxed paper.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Place a layer of 1/2 the corn chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 the chilies in casserole.
Repeat layers.
Cook onions rings in chicken broth for 5 minutes.
Arrange onion rings and pimento on casserole.
Pour broth over casserole. Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Start in cold oven.
Do not open door for 1 hour.
Cream butter and Crisco and add chocolate syrup, then add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk to cream mixture alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Pour over top and refrigerate.

title: 6 layer mexican dip
directions: Spray bottom of glass pan. Layer ingredients (amount to taste): refried beans, kidney beans or chili, olives +/or jalapeos, sour cream and salsa. Top with taco cheese. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. Serve with nacho chips.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in 9 x 13 inch pay.
Crumble brown sausage over bread, sprinkle cheese and mushrooms over top.
Combine eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups of the milk; pour over the ingredients in the pan.
Combine soup and remaining 1/2 cup of milk, pour over all.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: honey chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces and arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.
Serve with rice.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
eggs;
add
oil and water.
Mix well, then add all
dry
ingredients.	Cook in two loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Can substitute spices, if preferred.

title: mix in pan brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika; use mixture to coat chicken pieces.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thickened over medium heat. Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Fold in the strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Serve with spoonful of Cool Whip on top.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix together the cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Layer 1/3 of each of noodles, sauce and cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spanish gold cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: sweet 'n sour baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the bacon, in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix well.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients together.
Heat well.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in teriyaki sauce at least 2 hours. Broil or grill chicken until done.
Saute sliced onion and green pepper in margarine.
Top each chicken breast with equal portions of sauteed onion and green pepper.
Place approximately 1 ounce grated Monterey Jack on top of chicken breast with onion and green pepper.
Microwave until cheese is melted (about 1 minute).
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix well by hand.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: african-spiced vegetable salad
directions: Steam first 3 ingredients, covered, 2 minutes. Rinse under cold water; drain well. Combine salt and next 5 ingredients in small skillet. Place over medium heat 2 minutes or until fragrant, stirring constantly. Combine spice mixture, sour cream, vinegar and honey in medium bowl. Stir well. Add broccoli mixture and green onions; toss well to coat. Yields 2 servings of 1 cup each.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg yolks.
Add cocoa and hot water mixture, then add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and egg whites last.
Bake in two greased 10-inch layer cake pans
at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder, and salt with the oleo mixture.
Mix 1/4 cup of the flour with the berries and nuts and fold in.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 65 or 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on a wire rack.
Before serving, dust with confectioners sugar or make a glaze and drip it over cooled cake.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cool in 3-quart non-metal container.
Combine concentrates and sugar-water mixture; refrigerate.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and grenadine syrup; stir gently.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: avocado pie
directions: Peel avocado, remove pit and mash avocado.
Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Put in a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate at least two hours.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on cake box, adding a half a package of coconut.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and lightly floured pan.
Remove from oven while hot; punch holes with ice pick.
Mix sugar and milk thoroughly.
Pour over cake.
Let cool completely.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with the other half of coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday fruit cake (light)
directions: Note:
Yes a total of 3 cups flour, divided.

title: pop-up bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Stir together 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt over low heat only until warm, stirring to blend.
Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat until smooth, about 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer or 300 strokes by hand.

title: beet aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients. Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in bowl.
Combine milk with slightly beaten egg and oil.
Stir liquid and dry ingredients together lightly.
Add blueberries and mix well until all ingredients are just moistened.
Spray muffin cups with vegetable spray and fill 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baby cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and add the baby food. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, with low heat, melt chocolate with milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly on wax paper or buttered 8 x 8-inch dish or pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: beef pie
directions: Prepare buttermilk biscuits.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the water.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir bouillon into flour mixture all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add beef, peas, carrots and parsley; heat through.
Pour meat mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Place biscuits overlapping around edge of dish on top of boiling hot meat mixture.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix in all other ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Bake at 350° at least 1 hour.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Boil chicken, skin and debone;	saute onions in butter; add enchilada
mix
and all liquids.
Cook until it thickens. In
a casserole, layer chicken and Doritos;
cover each layer with sauce
and	cheese.
Repeat
until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
If tortillas are used, heat them one
at
a	time in a small amount of Wesson or any cooking oil, just long enough to soften;
drain and layer same as Doritos.

title: fudge(mmm, mmm, good)
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and melt together.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
With fork, combine cheese with margarine. Spread mixture on bread using about 1 1/2 teaspoons per slice. Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Cut each slice into 6 sticks. Place in single layer on large baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until brown and crisp.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and 1 cup salt in water to cover.
Add ice cubes and leave for 4 hours.
Rinse well.
Mix all other ingredients together; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and bring back to a boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Place in a large bowl with 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Shake until well covered.
Grease a Bundt pan and begin placing biscuits alternating with nuts until pan is filled.
In pan, bring butter, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Invert pan and let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in pan; cover and cook on low heat for 4 to
5 hours.
Stir to prevent sticking occasionally.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in deep cake pan.
Mix in a bowl the sugar, milk, baking powder and flour.
Pour mixture over butter. Pour the drained peaches on top of the batter.
Bake until brown.

title: cranberry jewel salad
directions: Stir jello in 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Mix in cranberry sauce.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold. Put in refrigerator until set.

title: mrs. truman's apple pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and stir into egg mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Stir well.
Pour into large, buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Tie spices in bag.
Heat to boiling point, then simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Place in cold packer (1/2 pints or pints).
Process for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Alternate flour, milk and extracts.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake in muffin tins at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening with spoon until well mixed.
Add milk gradually, mixing to form a soft ball. Sift 1/3 cup flour on board or waxed paper.
With rolling pin, roll out dough into a thin sheet.
Dot half of sheet with butter and fold other half over.
Fold again.
Handle quickly and roll out to desired thickness (1/2 to 1-inch).
Cut with floured cutter and put on ungreased baking sheet or pan.
Bake in hot oven at 400° to 425° until brown.

title: potting soil
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk together.
Alternate layers of mixture and Oreo cookies. Top off with cookies.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak across grain on a slight diagonal into thin strips. In a medium bowl, combine vinegar, soy sauce, garlic and ginger. Add beef slices and toss to coat.

title: nuts for chocolate bars(makes about 3 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup of the sugar in small bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup of margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of a greased, foil lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned or filling is set.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice and a few berries.
In mixing bowl combine flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Add oil, eggs and berries; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch loaf pans. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Beat cream cheese with reserved juice and berries to serve with bread.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except butter and sour cream) in heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
(Can also be cooked in microwave oven for 6 1/2 minutes on High; cook for 4 1/2 minutes, stir and continue cooking 2 minutes.)
Stir in butter and cool to room temperature.
Add sour cream and pour filling into baked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip; store in refrigerator.

title: festive cheese logs
directions: Soften Cheddar cheese and cream cheese to room temperature or place in microwave to soften.
Blend thoroughly.
It will take some time.
Add Tabasco, garlic powder and pecans.
Divide in half. Roll out into logs.
Sprinkle paprika on a piece of waxed paper and roll logs in it, coating generously.
Wrap each log in waxed paper and then in aluminum foil.
Makes 2 logs and freezes beautifully.

title: hot buttered rum cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar reserving 1/2 cup of sugar; add vanilla, lemon extract and egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add alternately flour and sour cream (with soda dissolved and stirred into sour cream); beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into first mixture and bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
While cake is still warm, cover with the Buttered Rum Glaze.

title: 5-minute chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a medium size saucepan over medium heat. Heat about 4 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: granola
directions: Mix together; pour into roast pan and toast at 250° until a golden brown (30 to 40 minutes).

title: cherry delight
directions: Whip Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly together. Put over graham cracker crust.
Put cherry pie filling on top. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan for this recipe.

title: creamy icing
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine, salt and granulated sugar.
Combine flour and milk.
Cook mixture to a paste, stirring constantly. Cool until lukewarm.
Add paste to creamed shortening.
Fold in powdered sugar to desired consistency.

title: chicken divine
directions: Put broccoli with chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Spread Cheddar cheese over mixture, then mix bread crumbs and oleo.
Pour on top of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blackened redfish
directions: Mix ingredients except fish thoroughly.
Cover fillets completely and cook on hot griddle or barbecue grill for a few minutes, depending on size of fillets.
Serve immediately.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding water until mixture is at desired consistency.
Pour oil in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put dish with oil only in a hot 400° oven.
Get dish hot for 5 minutes. Pour mix in pan and cook 30 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: cider salad mold
directions: In medium saucepan, bring to a boil cider, cloves and cinnamon. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 minutes; strain.
In medium bowl, stir hot cider mixture into gelatin until gelatin dissolves.
Pour 1 cup into 6-cup mold.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Set remaining gelatin aside at room temperature.
Arrange orange sections and apple slices in partially set gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Meanwhile, chill remaining gelatin mixture until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Gently stir in chopped apple. Spoon into mold over orange layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving dish.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sausage and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up side to form crust.
Seal holes.
Cook and drain sausage.
Pour over crust.
Mix cheeses together and sprinkle over sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, soda, vanilla and margarine.
Add corn syrup and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until tender.
Drain; stir in apples, sauerkraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook on low setting, stirring often.
Cook until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: marinated shrimp supreme
directions: In a large frying pan heat oil; add all ingredients except shrimp and lemon.
Cook slowly for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover; boil.
Lower heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices. Serve immediately with toothpicks.
Serves 6.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: On a large sheet of foil, form meat into a loaf about 3-inches thick. Sprinkle soup mix over meat. Spoon soup over top of meat loaf. Wrap loosely with foil and seal tightly.
Place in a shallow pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.
Gravy will be greasy unless lean beef is used.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook rapidly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper or greased counter.
After cookies have cooled off a little, put in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break fresh broccoli into small flowerets.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Thinly slice red onion.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir until all coated.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Open the cans of garbanzo beans and kidney beans; drain them in the colander.
While they are draining, brown the hamburger and follow the directions on the taco seasoning package.
Let the hamburger cool a little bit.

title: beef and cheddar macaroni
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain fat.
In a large bowl, combine beef and onion, spaghetti sauce, macaroni, 1 cup cheese, mushrooms, basil, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350°, for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: rena's candied yams
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes in dishpan.
Put in jars and seal.
Pressure 5 minutes on 10 pounds of pressure.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, then drain.
Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Butter a two quart casserole and pour mixture in.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef in casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover and place in 350° oven for 3 hours; stir every hour.

title: busy woman's dream
directions: Crumble hamburger in bottom of 9 x 9-inch or slightly larger pan.
Spread soup evenly over it and place potato puffs on top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: janice's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, blended oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
Mix together with creamed ingredients and add a 12 ounce bag of mini chocolate chips, 1 (8 ounce) Hershey bar (grated) and 3 cups chopped nuts (any kind).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove cookies and place on wire rack to cool.
Eat cookies.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Drain shrimp.
Rinse in cold water.
Soak in ice 20 minutes. Devein and mash shrimp.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add 1/2 stick of butter, cheese, mustard and lemon juice.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
With remaining 1/2 stick of melted butter, mix with cracker crumbs and spread over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef roll
directions: Chop 1 package beef and mix with cream cheese, chopped onions and Worcestershire.
Form into a ball and roll in second package of beef (chopped).
Chill.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, combine pineapple juice, water, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink.
Add remaining ingredients except rice; cook until heated through. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gourmet style steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces; rub each piece on both sides with cut garlic clove.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper; pound into steak.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Top with onions and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 2 hours.
Add more liquid, if needed.
Remove steak to platter. Spoon excess fat from liquid in pan; add sour cream.
If too thick, dilute with 1/2 cup water or bouillon.
Heat and serve sauce over meat.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pot, heat water and bouillon cubes.
When boiling, add macaroni.
Cook according to package instructions until just al dente.
Drain well.
Cut ham into small strips.
Place a layer of pasta over bottom of a lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle with ham. Continue to layer pasta and ham.
In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over macaroni. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Mix well. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Serves 8 generously.

title: butter nut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely; roll again in powdered sugar.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.
Grease a baking sheet. Combine all ingredients and mix well, using a food processor, fitted with the steel blade, or an electric mixer.
This dough will be sticky and soft but don't add any more flour.
Place on a well-floured surface and sprinkle just a little flour on top of the dough.
Knead about 10 times. Roll or pat out to a thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter.

After cutting the biscuits, you can roll the scraps of dough again but do this only once. Place the biscuits about 2 inches apart on the baking sheet. Bake for about 10 minutes or until the tops are light golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese in milk.
Add all remaining ingredients except potato chips.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers; dot top with butter.
Bake until top becomes bubbly.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the hamburger; add salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: a new yorker's linguini and clam sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Drain clams, saving 1 cup of clam juice.
Add clam juice, olive oil, spices and clams to sauteed onion and butter.
Cook on medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve over linguini and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Bake sweet potatoes to 400° for 1 hour.
Peel and cut diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange potatoes in 14-inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, honey, Southern Comfort, cinnamon and nutmeg in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over sweet potatoes and apples and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, the last 5 minutes brown under broiler.

title: a want last cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat well.
Bake in a prepared tube or Bundt pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Also may be baked in a sheath pan.

title: oriental salad
directions: Place noodles in real warm water.
Let soak until soft. Drain.
Chop or slice cabbage.
Cut onions, including the green tops. Mix softened noodles with cabbage, onions and water chestnuts.

title: ginger "snappies"
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg very thoroughly.
Add spices and molasses.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to other ingredients. Chill.
Form in nut sized balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: triple bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, cider vinegar, salt and pepper together.
Toss with vegetables and refrigerate 6 hours.
Mix several times before serving.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: *Eight tablespoons of honey may be used instead of sugar.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Pour in 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: short ribs with lima beans
directions: Rinse limas, add the 5 cups water.
Boil 2 minutes, remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Brown ribs in skillet, remove excess fat.
Bury ribs in limas and add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook gently until meat and limas are tender.
If needed, add more water, season with salt and pepper to taste in the last 1/2 hour.

title: potato-patch casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion, egg, milk, bread crumbs and seasonings. Mix lightly.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
Brown in oil.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup of the flour, the sugars, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining 3/4 cup of flour.
If necessary, cover and chill dough until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
If desired roll in additional sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until bottoms lightly brown. Immediately after baking press 1 milk chocolate kiss into each cookie.

title: fried green tomatoes with cornmeal
directions: Slice each about 1/2-inch thick, then pat cut surface dry with paper towel.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in pie plate. Dredge tomato slices in seasoned cornmeal, making sure each slice is well coated.
Fry tomatoes quickly in sizzling hot bacon fat in heavy skillet over moderately high heat.
Need only to brown slices on each side, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes to each side should do it.
Serve straight away.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Knead and spread on greased platter.
Cut into pieces.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Blend all together.
Put in pan and let sit in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 12 to 15.
Good for a luncheon.

title: jack-pot hamburger meal
directions: Brown beef, onion and green peppers in a large skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients except noodles.
Cook noodles by boiling 15 minutes until tender.
Drain and sprinkle noodles over top of skillet mixture and simmer all for several minutes to absorb liquid.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix
all
dry ingredients.
Melt margarine and mix with orange juice and water. Beat egg slightly and add to juice and water mixture.
Mix liquids into dry ingredients. Add nuts and cranberries
which have been washed and cut into halves.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
Peel and slice potatoes; put on top of pork chops.
Add celery soup on top of pork chops and potatoes.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: candy turtles
directions: Mix candy caramels and milk; heat until candy is melted.
Then mix nuts in candy and spoon onto wax paper.
Melt chocolate and dip candy in it until well coated.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: play dough
directions: Playing with play dough is lots of fun and helps to strengthen small hand muscles as well as encouraging creativity!

title: banana pudding with sugar biscuits
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil, whisking constantly, 1 minute.
Remove from heat, and stir in butter and vanilla.
Line bottom of a trifle bowl or large clear bowl with one-third of banana slices and one-third of pudding. Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Beat whipping cream at medium speed with an electric mixer until foamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Spread evenly over pudding.
Serve with Sugar Biscuits.

title: coney island manwiches
directions: In
skillet,
cook
ground
beef until done; drain fat. Stir in
Manwich, mustard, Worcestershire and salt until well blended. Arrange hot dogs
in
meat mixture; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Turn hot
dogs occasionally.
Open buns slightly; toast lightly. Place hot
dogs
in
buns;
spoon meat mixture down center.
Top with shredded
cheese.
Makes
8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna casserole(microwave)
directions: Boil noodles and then drain. Rinse and place into a casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and tuna.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in microwave for 15 minutes on High.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and plain gelatin in boiling water; blend in the cream cheese until smooth.
Add soup and blend well.
Cool. Add mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, lemon juice and sugar, if desired. Beat until well blended.
Chill gelatin mixture until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: golden punch
