directions: Mix everything but 7-Up together and refrigerate overnight. Add ice and 7-Up when ready to serve.
Number of servings:

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, butter, milk and lemon juice.
Mix together and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's old fashion ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour contents into ice cream mixer.
Add milk to within 1/2-inch of top, put lid on churn and add ice and rock salt while turning crank.

title: soft buns, rolls or bread
directions: Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Roll up and cut, placing cut side down in pan.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan at 250° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate crunchies
directions: Melt together peanut butter and shortening over low heat.
Add candies.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly with metal spoon.
Press candies to break up.
Remove from heat.
Add corn flakes, mixing until thoroughly coated.
Drop by rounded 1/2 teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 1 or 2 additional candies into mixture if desired.
Let stand until set, about 30 minutes.
Makes about 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fudge
directions: Mix in large bowl first 5 ingredients.
Boil sugar and milk in a large pan for 6 minutes.
Pour sugar mixture over the ingredients in the large bowl and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into greased pans to set.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until shortening is dissolved and cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water and the egg.
Mix well.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Spread layer of potatoes in casserole dish.
Press down. Sprinkle with cheese and onion.
Spread another layer of potatoes followed by a layer of cheese and onion; continue layers until casserole is full, pressing down on potatoes each time.
Add Worcestershire to cream until mixture looks like coffee with cream.
Pour over potatoes and press down again.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
I made this up myself.
Everyone loves it!

title: molded potato salad*
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel.
Cut in thin slices.
Chop onion, pepper and pimientos.
Lightly oil a standard loaf pan.
Mix onion, pepper, pimiento, mayonnaise, curry powder and salt.
Arrange layer of potato slices in bottom of pan. Spread with mayonnaise.
Alternate potatoes and the mixture until all ingredients are used.
Press down firmly.
Chill.
Unmold onto salad greens.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375°.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the meat, in a bowl that has an airtight lid.
This is the marinade.
Cut the meat into strips about 1/8-inch thick.
Stir the meat in the marinade to coat all sides.
Cover and refrigerate 3 days to a week.
Remove strips. Blot off excess moisture.
Place strips on racks in the oven so that the strips are not touching.
Set the oven at the lowest possible temperature and maintain.
Keep oven door slightly ajar. Cook 4 to 12 hours until the meat is no longer moist.
Store jerky in airtight container.
May be wrapped in freezer paper and stored in freezer.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until no indention when pressed with finger.

title: pudding jello salad
directions: Blessed is the salt added to sugar for cooked icing to keep it from graining.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and flour. Add egg yolks, evaporated milk and vanilla and mix well. Add enough milk to make mixture to be 2 quarts. Place in microwave and cook until thick. Layer in a baking dish the vanilla wafers, bananas and pour on pudding mixture. Repeat layers.

title: chile con queso
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add and melt the cheese.
Drain and crush in hands the tomatoes.
Add to melted cheese.
Chop fine (in blender) the hot finger peppers.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add little salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Toss hash browns, cheese and onion together with enough flour to coat ingredients well.
Place in a greased casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter.
Add milk to about 1/4 of dish. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: simply good and delicious
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Stir in flour gradually.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Spread pie filling on top and then cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cut when cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, beat in the shortening, eggs milk, and vanilla.
Add the apples and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13.
Bake 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Drizzle some thick white frosting across the top.

title: yule chiffon cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Make a well and add the oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites in large bowl.
Beat until whites form stiff peaks.
Do not underbeat.
Gently fold egg whites into the batter.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer soup mixture, salad dressing and preserves on stove top for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put sausage in one quart casserole dish.
Pour cooled mixture over them. Marinate overnight.	Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yield 1 quart.

title: chocolate chip pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1/3 cup oil in 9 x 13-inch pan. Tilt pan until oil covers the whole bottom of pan.
Empty contents of cake mix and pudding in the pan over the oil.
Add 1 1/3 cup of water and 2 eggs.
Mix well with fork, making sure you mix the oil as well with it.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the mixture and blend well.
Scrape sides.
Put in oven for 30 minutes or until done by touch.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Do not boil.
Take from heat; stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato slices.
Dot with dressing and butter.
Cover with corned beef and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven.
Separate each biscuit into 3 layers.
Slightly overlap biscuit layers on casserole to form three rows.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until biscuit topping is slightly brown.

title: greek chicken with cheese
directions: Place the Feta cheese in a bowl with cold water to cover.
Set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a 10-inch skillet with a cover.
Brown the chicken breasts over moderate heat.
Transfer to a platter.
Add the teaspoon of oil to the skillet along with sliced onions.
Cook the onions over a moderately low heat, stirring them, for about ten minutes.
Add the garlic and cook for another 5 minutes or until the onions start to brown.
Add the tomatoes with liquid and the oregano, stirring to combine.
Place the chicken on top of the sauce.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover the pan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove the Feta from the water and arrange on top of the chicken.
Cover and simmer for a few minutes, until cheese is melted.
Good served over spinach noodles, ordinary noodles or rice.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat about 20 strokes.
Allow dough to rise about 5 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Divide dough in half.
Place on greased baking sheet. Spread to 10-inches round.
Continue flouring hand while spreading dough.
Add pizza ingredients and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix ground beef, taco seasoning and beans.
In a deep 9 x 13-inch pan, make a layer of tortillas by tearing and fitting 2 or a bit more to cover bottom of pan.
Spread over a third of the beef mixture, then a third of the shredded cheese.
Layer on. Spread sour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine cider and ale.
Put in bottom of 30-cup percolator. Place remaining ingredients in basket and let perk.
Serve hot.

title: chewy noels
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over melted butter. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°, cool.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken and potatoes
directions: Clean chicken.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put chicken in Dutch oven.
Place potatoes and the soup mixed with water and milk in pan. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: crystal pie
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in an uncooked pie crust.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a medium sized bowl and transfer to an ungreased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chilly soup
directions: In a blender, whirl together equal amounts of buttermilk and fresh berries or peaches.
Sweeten to taste with honey or sugar. Chill at least 2 hours.
Top with fruit and serve.

title: diabetic bar cookies
directions: Place margarine in a cup and melt in microwave.
Beat eggs and sweetener until fluffy.
Add flavoring, flour and baking powder. Blend in margarine.
Stir in nuts, raisins, prunes and coconut. Pour in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Remove.
If runny, add a little more oatmeal until thick.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until sausage is browned on all sides.

title: apricot glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water (salted), about 10 minutes or until tender.
Cool, peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Arrange in dish.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix 3 cups water, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and oil.
Add the yeast mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Continue adding flour until mixture is soft and sticky.
Put on floured board and knead.
Put in large bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and pinch off dough balls.
Put 2 balls in greased muffin pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.
Brush with margarine.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large covered casserole.
Bake in oven for 5 hours at 250°.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash until smooth.
Add all ingredients and beat.
Refrigerate, covered. Keeps for about 2 weeks.
Place desired amount in buttered casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or microwave a small dipper on a plate or in individual serving dish.

title: tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Simmer onion and garlic in hot pan until yellow.
Add meat and brown.
Pour off excess grease.
Then add to tomatoes.
Pour mixture into square baking dish.
Press olives into mixture.
Combine cornmeal, milk and eggs.
Spoon over filling; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: eclair cake
directions: Boil water and oleo or heat in microwave until oleo melts. Add flour and mix together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Spread onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Slit bubbles in dough after baking.
Cool.

title: sausage and lima bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container.
Beat with electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together for 8 minutes; add the tea and chill.
When thoroughly chilled, add the remaining ingredients; pour over ice in tall glasses and serve.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife, cut beef across grain, into thin strips. Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss and stir over medium-high heat until browned.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes (until tender).
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan.
Cook until thick.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in a baking dish.
Salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Cut up cabbage and lay on top of potatoes.
Cut sausage into 2-inch pieces; then slice down middle.
Lay on top of cabbage.
Add 3/4 cup of water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: home fried potatoes
directions: Wash and slice as many red potatoes as needed.
Leave peelings on.
Place in skillet that has 1/2 inch oil in bottom. Cut onion over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with lid; cook over low heat until tender.
Remove lid and brown on both sides. Serve with white beans and cornbread.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over top of pecans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar and flavoring.
Knead until all sugar is thoroughly blended.
Shape into 8 rolls; wrap each in plastic and freeze.

title: mandarin orange gelatin
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and chill.
Place fruit in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When gelatin begins to congeal, pour over fruit.
Chill.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Cook about 1 hour.
Keep warm for serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Cut chicken into pieces and layer on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all of the ingredients, except stuffing
and cheese, in separate pan and heat until margarine is melted.
Pour over chicken.
Place thin slices of Velveeta cheese on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with prepared stuffing.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup and broth.
Spoon over chicken.
Arrange potatoes and mixed vegetables over chicken.
Mix flour and baking powder in a bowl; add butter and buttermilk and stir to form a thin dough. Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until crust rises to top and is browned lightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan with butter.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and roll into a ball.
Dip balls into mixture of sugar and cinnamon and layer into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle additional cinnamon, sugar and nuts thru layers.
Cook margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon over low heat until margarine and sugar melts.
Pour over top of layered dough balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss cheese pie
directions: This is the first step in many French-Canadian (cajun) dishes. Rice dressings, gumbos, jambalaya, Etouffee, eggplant casseroles, etc. and vegetable soup use roux.

title: granny's pecan roll
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar and vanilla, kneading the last of the sugar gradually.
Shape into 8 rolls, 1 inch in diameter.
Wrap and put in freezer overnight.
Melt caramels in double boiler, adding a teaspoon of water at a time, until thick sauce-like consistency and all caramels are melted.
Remove from heat, but keep over hot water.
Dip rolls into caramels, then roll in chopped pecans.
Press firmly into caramel with hands.
Let cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: feather-light crust
directions: Have shortening at room temperature.
Cut it into the flour and salt.
Add egg and vinegar and part of the water.
Be certain water is cold and use only enough to make a firm ball.
Chill if you wish.
Roll into 2 crusts.
If it seems easier to roll on wax paper, then do so.
Never stretch the crust when fitting to the pan.
For soft pies, prick crusts and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix well.
Use loaf pans greased and lined with wax paper. Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand.
Mix well, then mix in the lemon juice and vanilla; pour on crust. Chill until top is firm and top with cherries.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine together and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Spread on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan crisp
directions: Mix the margarine, plain flour and 2 cups brown sugar together.
Pat in an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Pour thawed lemonade into a large bowl.
Squeeze the juice from the lemon into lemonade.
Add Cool Whip to lemonade mixture and stir, then add the Eagle Brand milk; stir until blended.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill for 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: chinese tea eggs
directions: Place the eggs in a saucepan of cold water.
Bring them to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil them for 25 minutes.
Cool the eggs for 5 minutes in cold water.
Lightly roll the eggs on a flat surface until their shells are covered with fine cracks.
Place the eggs in a large saucepan.
Add the other ingredients.
Add sufficient water to cover.
Bring them just to boiling.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: shoney strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Add Jell-O.
Put strawberries in cooked pie shell. Pour mixture over berries. Cool. Top with whipped cream and refrigerate.

title: delicious moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be runny.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and garlic in a 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave at High until beef is brown (5 to 9 minutes), stirring once to break up beef.
Drain.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix all together with clean hands.
Store in airtight container.
Eat some now and save the rest for later.
Yum!

title: pumpkin bread with coconut
directions: Grease and flour 8 small loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking pans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: judy's best taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans with picante sauce and spread on 14-inch platter.
Mix softened cream cheese with taco seasoning and spread on top of refried beans.
Mash avocados and mix with guacamole mix; spread on top of cream cheese.
Layer olives, onions and tomatoes and top with grated cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve. It will keep a couple of weeks in the refrigerator, if desired, in an airtight container.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook in a double boiler.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until a hard ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Pour cooked mixture over beaten egg whites (that have been beaten stiff).
Add nuts and vanilla and beat until it starts to harden.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into a bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg, peel and juice, all at once.
Stir until moist.
Fold in raisins and berries. Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pan at 350° for one hour and thirty minutes.

title: melissa's pizza rolls
directions: Unthaw bread as directed on package.
Let bread rise, then roll out on floured board.
Roll as thin as you can.
Spread pizza sauce on (thin layer of sauce), then pepperoni and cheese.
Roll up.
Bake on cookie sheet for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bread (white)
directions: In a measuring cup, put shortening and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add two more cups warm water.
To this, add sugar, salt and crumbled yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour until it doesn't stick to fingers.
Grease all over with butter and put in large pan to double in bulk (about 45 minutes).

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over a medium heat, stirring constantly.
(Mixture will scorch easy.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until blended well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat 2 or 3 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread crushed onions evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pudding chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar together.
Stir in pudding.
Beat eggs lightly and stir them into pudding mixture.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into pudding mixture.
Blend well and fold in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: lenten chocolate cake
directions: Measure flour, soda, cocoa,
salt
and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Add vinegar,
vanilla, oil and water;
mix well. Pour batter into greased pan
x
13-inches).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Combine crab, cheese, onion and dill.
Set aside.
In saucepan melt butter and stir in flour; cook 2 minutes.
Combine milk and soup.
Add soup mixture with flour mixture and season to taste. Add few tablespoons of sauce to crab mixture.
Set remaining sauce aside.

title: kringle
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out into rectangles, 12 x 8-inches wide. Put on greased cookie sheet before filling.
Place filling in the middle and fold edges over.
Seal ends.
Brush top with beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until tender.
Drain well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix 1/4 cup Cheddar and sour cream.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers mixed with 3/4 cup cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sun city rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Shred cheeses and mix together.
In large shallow pan (a lasagna pan works well), layer 1/2 rice, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 shredded cheeses.
Sprinkle lightly with onion and garlic powder, if desired.
Layer remaining rice, cottage cheese and shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and just begins to brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix together sifted flour and sugar.
Put butter, oil, Coca-Cola and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour hot into sugar and flour mixture.
Add to mixture while beating eggs and vanilla.
Mix together first, then add to mixture, sour milk and baking soda.
After all is mixed, fold in mini marshmallows and mixed chopped nuts.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Leave cake in pan and cool.

title: broiled mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika and mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushrooms and fill caps with mixture.
Top with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Add salt and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and coconut. Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper and let set.

title: lima beans and mushrooms
directions: Open beans and mushrooms. Mix well and pour into baking dish. Make a thin cream sauce and pour over this mixture.
Season to taste.
Top dish with grated cheese and buttered bread crumbs. Bake in 450° oven about 30 minutes.

title: seven layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Then add 2 cups real mayonnaise mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Dot over salad and spread carefully over top to sides.
Add 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top; bacon bits, if desired.
Make the night before.

title: pastel mint dessert
directions: Put half of the crushed Oreos in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip the cream and add marshmallows and mint.
Spread over layer of Oreos.
Sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate for 2 days before serving.
The mints will melt into the rest of the ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except has browns; fold hash browns into mixture. Bake in 9 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: o-henry bars
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and press into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread over oatmeal mixture and refrigerate until hard.

title: almost reese's bars
directions: Melt margarine in large bowl in microwave.
Stir in sugar, peanut butter and cracker crumbs.
Pat out in jelly roll cake pan. Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Spread over mixture.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: tuna pat
directions: Mix together; shape into large ball. Roll into walnuts and chill.

title: congealed sunshine salad
directions: Blend jello,
cream
cheese
and
salt; stir in boiling water, stirring until mixture dissolves.
Add reserved pineapple and orange syrup; mix well.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken. Fold in pineapple, orange sections and pecans.
Pour into 1 large mold
or
12 small molds; refrigerate until congealed.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut in bite size pieces. Cook broccoli pieces. Put chicken and broccoli in a 2-quart casserole. Cut strips of Velveeta cheese and place on top of the chicken and broccoli. Spread the celery soup on top of these ingredients. Make Stove Top stuffing thin enough to spread over top of all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: citrus-curry chicken breasts
directions: Combine the orange and lime juices, the garlic, curry powder, salt and several grindings of black pepper.
Put the chicken into a glass pan and pour the marinade over.
The chicken can be marinated 15 minutes at room temperature or several hours in the refrigerator.

title: hello dollies
directions: Make graham cracker crust and press into the bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour milk over top of layered ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan tart
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Put sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and butter into large bowl. Beat until smooth. Pour into pie shell. Arrange pecans in circles on top of filling. Bake for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 350°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until crust is golden and filling is set. Cool on wire rack.

title: microwave bacon-wrapped triscuits
directions: Wrap 1 slice bacon around each cracker.
Place in a circle on several layers of paper towels.
Microwave on High for several minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: galliano cake(a prize winning pillsbury contest recipe)
directions: Mix water and Tang together.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl at low speed until moist, then beat another 4 minutes with electric beater at medium speed.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
When done, turn upside-down on plate lined with wax paper.
Then turn over and sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.
Be sure cake is cooled before adding powdered sugar.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Chop onion and green pepper; cook to the tender stage in butter (do not brown).
Blend in flour, then add milk and stir until thick.
Add cheese, salt, nutmeg and crabmeat.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and halve apples; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Pour in milk; stir with a fork until mixture resembles pie crust dough.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Spread chopped up meat in the bottom of greased baking dish. Spread choice of vegetable over meat.
Mix choice of soup with other ingredients until thin.
Pour over vegetables and meat layers.
Spread crushed croutons over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for using up those leftovers!

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine rice and boiling water in large saucepan (mixture of wild and brown rice can be used).
Simmer, covered, for 50 to 60 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove bacon and saute onion, celery and carrots in small amount of bacon fat.
Combine broth, soup, milk, mushrooms, salt, pepper, reserved bacon, sauteed vegetables and wild rice.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese boat
directions: Mix all together.
Fill boat and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels in milk; add margarine.
Remove cake from oven. Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Add nuts and chips.
Pour remaining batter over top and bake 20 minutes at 250°, then another 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost with chocolate icing when cool. Enjoy!

title: beer cheese soup
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine soup, sugar, garlic salt, pepper and milk.
Heat to simmering.
Stir in beer.
Ladle into mugs or bowls.
Top servings with crumbled crackers or popcorn and parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german style pot roast(for crock pot)
directions: Sear roast on all sides, then put in crock pot with other ingredients.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons butter, then add to other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broiled garlic shrimp
directions: Combine garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, butter and pepper in a bowl.
Add shrimp and stir until coated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil together peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy pan until taffy color (approximately 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and add soda and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into shallow buttered pan.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sliced peaches and sprinkle the sugar, jello and butter on top and add water slowly.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts; form in a ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap and chill for 24 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Add flour, soda and extracts.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Stir together and cook in electric rice cooker.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water.
Drain.
Combine milk and soup.
Pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can of onions.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remainder of onions.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower delight
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs with snacking sauce
directions: Mix well beef, potatoes, onions, seasonings and cream.
Roll the mixture into marble size balls.
Chill them until cold.
Roll balls in mixture of flour and cheese.
Brown them in margarine and drain.
Place meatball and tomato wedge on a toothpick or skewer and serve with snacking sauce in a chafing dish.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight. Place in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, arrange in single layer half of the cookies, half of the bananas, half of the glaze and half of whipped topping.
Repeat layers.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Sift together flour and sugar into mixing bowl. Stir in cheese and onion. Blend together egg, milk and oil. Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened. Turn into greased 5 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack several minutes before removing. Slice in large pieces and serve warm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mashed potatoes should already be seasoned. Add eggs and flour until sticky and will hold a patty shape. Fry in a thin layer of grease until golden brown and insides are heated.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients, holding back 1 cup pastry flour and the bran.
Mix oil and maple syrup.
Add eggs; mix.
Add milk quickly; mix.
Add wet to the dry mixture with a spatula until fairly smooth.
Add bananas, remaining flour and bran; mix just until wet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.
Yields approximately 24 muffins.

title: st. louis gooey cake
directions: Put cake mix into large bowl.
Add melted oleo or butter and 2 eggs.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Mix together sugar and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs; mix and pour over first mixture in pan and "tuck" around sides.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rancher's bean pot
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Remove from pan.
Pour off drippings, reserving 1/4 cup.
Brown onion and flour in reserved drippings.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish or bean pot.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, pepperoni and	mushrooms
in
skillet. Start noodles.
Drain mixtures.
Add
sauce.
Simmer
10	minutes.
In lightly greased 9 x 12 x
2-inch pan, layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella (about 3 slices), sauce mixture and Provolone. Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: punch recipe
directions: Mix jello and sugar in large plastic container.
Add boiling water and mix until dissolved.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Pour into gallon plastic container and freeze.
When ready to use, set out approximately 2 hours.
Add 1/2 bottle ginger ale to 1 gallon frozen mixture.
Serves about 25.

title: icebox biscuits
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water with yeast and buttermilk.
Add all this to your flour.
Mix and roll out.
Cut out with biscuit butter.
Butter them; fold half back.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, serve in place of jelly and such.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put all spices into tea ball.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: vegetable rice bake
directions: In a saucepan, combine bouillon granules and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to boiling; add rice.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine green pepper and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add shredded zucchini or chopped broccoli.
Cover and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain well.
Set aside.

title: crab meat balls
directions: Drain and flake crab meat.
Combine with remaining ingredients except bacon.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Wrap with bacon. Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon crisp (under medium heat) 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn to brown evenly.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions on box.
Line bottom of baking dish or pan with 1/2 of stuffing.
Cube chicken and spread on top of stuffing.
If using mushrooms, spread over chicken. Combine milk and soup and pour over top of chicken; add other half of Stove Top stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add the sauce and water; simmer. Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs together.
Cook noodles in salt water; drain and separate.
Cover 9 x 13-inch dish with 1 cup sauce.
Top with 3 to 4 noodles.
Add 1 cup sauce next, then portion of cheese mixture.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
To complete, top with layer of noodles and sauce only. Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Separate wings.
Cut off tips.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Drain. Save marinade. Place wings in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush with marinade.
Turn and bake 30 minutes more.

title: honey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using 2 teaspoons butter, grease 5 3/4 x 5 1/2-inch mini loaf pans.

title: butter rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add water and mix well. Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of the sugar and cinnamon. Roll jelly roll fashion and cut into 1 1/2-inch thick slices. Place in buttered pan and bake at 370° for 20 minutes.
While rolls are baking, heat milk and remaining sugar over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over rolls and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: confetti rice
directions: Combine tomato juice and vegetables in medium saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and pepper.
Cover and turn off.

title: chinese chicken finger batter
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Use to coat chicken breast slices, shrimp or pork.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: three bean salad
directions: Heat vinegar, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over rest of ingredients in glass or crock bowl.
Let refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mash the potatoes and blend in oleo. Add balance of ingredients. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread about 1-inch thick in pan. Cook until brown at 350° to 370°. Cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients.
Soak	chicken
in bowl overnight or several hours. Place
chicken
in	roasting pan and bake until golden brown. Turn over
the	chicken
and brown.
It takes about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut maraschino cherries in half; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat 2 egg whites at high speed, scraping bowl often, until soft peaks form; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 egg yolks, 2 cups sugar, butter and chocolate.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Add flour, baking soda and salt alternately with cherry buttermilk mixture. Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Fold in cherries, then egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Remove from pans, then cool completely before frosting between each layer and entire cake.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into baking pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Store leftover cake in loosely covered dish in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce into a large bowl.
Layer onion, celery, green pepper and peas over lettuce.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well.
Spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar over sour cream mixture.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Decorate top with cherry tomatoes.

title: dad's meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll into loaf form and put in baking dish.
Rub a coating of ketchup on the top and sides of the meatloaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Blend sugar, butter, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll out on waxed paper until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 325° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: old mcdonald's cat creek chili
directions: Brown
ground beef over an open fire, if possible, in a well-seasoned
iron
skillet,
stirring
continuously.
When thoroughly
cooked,
transfer to cast-iron pot and remove from fire
temporarily.
Saute
the
chopped
Vidalia
onions
and Georgia
bell
peppers in the garlic in the black skillet with grease from the meat.
Add some cow butter or lard if the beef is too
lean.
Add
browned
onion,
garlic
and green pepper mixture to beef in iron pot, stirring in thoroughly, over the open
fire, being
careful not to get too many ashes into the pot.
Add tomato
sauce,
kidney
beans with Cat Creek water, whatever elixir you have chosen (last resort vinegar will do) and Worcestershire
sauce.
Mix
with wooden spoon thoroughly while adding
chili
powder,
oregano,
cumin and crushed red peppers. Put
back over fire and simmer for 2 or 3 hours (the longer
the better).
If
chili
is
too thick to suit, add a little onion soup or bouillon.
This recipe should serve about 10 people, depending on the weather and the kind of work going on that day.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Brown beef and onions together in a skillet until golden brown.
In a greased casserole pan, make a 1/4-inch layer of mashed potatoes.
Alternate with a layer of beef and onion mixture.
Make as many layers as desired, topping is with mashed potatoes.
Spread the milk over this and dot with butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with a salad and a vegetable.

title: famous sweet and sour dressing
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in saucepan and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Do not boil.
Cool and whip in oil.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add shortening; blend until fine and mealy.
Add vinegar and egg.
Add 1 tablespoon water at a time.
Yield: 2 pie crusts.
May be frozen for later use.
Allow to thaw before cooking.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Boil and cool the first 3 ingredients. Add the pineapple juice, strawberries and pink lemonade.
Freeze in ice cream pail. Stir occasionally. Before serving, add the 7-Up.

title: caramel-nut corn
directions: Divide popcorn and nuts between 2 ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt over medium heat.
Stir occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking five minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn and nuts, stirring until corn is well coated.
Bake, uncovered, in a 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes for one hour.
Makes 15 servings at 300 calories per serving.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pack firmly in spring-form pan.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, baking cocoa and eggs in mixer bowl; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until set.
Cool in pan.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: frances' egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, sugar and milk well. Gradually add extract, mixing all the ingredients together.
Now add cornstarch; be sure to blend this in well to avoid lumps. Blend in nutmeg.
Stir; now add the butter.
Pour into pie shell. Garnish top of pie with nutmeg.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate 12 eggs.
Beat whites stiff and add 1/2 cup sugar. Fold in and set aside.
Beat yellows and add 1 cup sugar; add 1 pint or more whiskey to yellows and sugar, then add the milk and the whipped cream to egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites and chill. Makes about 1 3/4 gallons.
Better if made night before serving.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in jar; cover until ready to use.
Place 2 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water; stir and serve.

title: sharon lease keilholtz's holiday punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in sugar; add juices and water and stir until thawed.
Pour into 1 large or several small freezer containers.
Add some orange slices and maraschino cherries and freeze.
When ready to use, place frozen mix in punch bowl and add several liter bottles of ginger ale.
Add more ginger ale as needed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in sugar, oil and zucchini.
Mix well, then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased bread pans and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Marinate the first four ingredients for a minimum of four hours.
After marinating, drain off Italian dressing and add mayonnaise.
The mayonnaise should be just enough to coat the salad.
Chill.
Add the cheese and bacon just prior to serving. This recipe can be used as a salad or a dip with frito corn chips.

title: candied yams
directions: Combine in buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lyla dee's quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place in bottom of a greased casserole.
Pour sauce over beef, then add cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together baking soda and buttermilk.
Do first.
Let set while fixing rest.

title: cabbage rolls kaldomar(sweden)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Add meats and rice. Beat together. Steam cabbage leaves until limp.
Drain.
Place ball of meat mixture on each leaf at the thin end part; fold in sides and roll heavy vein part to the top. Fasten with a toothpick.
Place rolls in baking dish.
Blend soup, brown sugar and salt together.
Add water, if desired.
Pour over cabbage rolls. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done. Serve with boiled potatoes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a very large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Keeps up to 6 weeks.
To bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pans with cooking spray.
Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well; set aside in another bowl.
Using fork or wire whisk, mix egg whites, water and corn syrup well.
Add flour mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Put 1 teaspoon of mix in upper triangle of wrapper.
Fold points together and seal with egg yolk and water mix.
Pinch long ends together.
Fry in hot oil until golden.
Serve with sweet-sour sauce or hot mustard.

title: good country eatin' oklahoma okra
directions: Layer all ingredients in buttered casserole dish, except for cheese and some bread crumbs.
(Beat the cornstarch and stock together, then add to ingredients.)
Sprinkle remaining bread cubes on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° to 400°, then top with the cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: sausage spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Stir and cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add sausage mixture to spaghetti and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and bake in a large pie dish at 250° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut top off after cooled.
Stir berries and Cool Whip together and put on crust.
Top with crust that you cut off.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs, then add the sugar, syrup, melted butter, vanilla and salt; stir well.
Add pecans last.
Stir and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun crock-pot cabbage
directions: Layer cabbage, potatoes and onions.
Add salt and pepper lightly because ham will have some salt.
Sprinkle a few flakes of parsley and bay leaf.
Drizzle with melted butter, then layer with ham.
Repeat.
Make several holes through casserole.
Pour tomato bits and water.
Cover and simmer several hours until vegetables are tender.

title: iowa steak
directions: Pound steak, dredge in flour, cut meat into 3-inch cubes. Simmer onion in oil until golden brown, remove from pan.
Brown steak, add salt, pepper, onions, water, sour cream and horseradish.
Cook very slowly for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple broccoli salad
directions: Toss main ingredients and fruit in large bowl, add 1/3 c. salad dressing.
Stir into main ingredients and fruit.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour crushed potato chips.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: sausage and apple quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prebake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Cook sausage with onion until brown.
Drain excess fat.
Toss sausage and onion, apples and cheese together.
Spoon into shell.
Beat eggs with cream, sage and nutmeg.
Pour into shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until firm.
Let stand 5 minutes then serve.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl for 2 minutes, or until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate for 1 1/4 hours, or until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Refrigerate until mixture will mound, about 10 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, or until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small flowerettes.
Chop next five ingredients very fine.
Pour salad dressing over mixture and let set in refrigerator.
Before serving, sprinkle with poppy seed and garlic salt.

title: fresh mushroom soup(sour)
directions: Wash mushrooms and cook in 1 quart of water until tender. Strain (save water).
Run mushrooms through food chopper.
Add sauerkraut juice to mushroom water.
Salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Brown flour in butter until brown; add onion and brown.
Add 1/4 cup water and bring to a boil and stir.
Strain; add to sauerkraut and mushroom juice with mushrooms and simmer for a couple minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 2 or 3 loaf pans. In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and allspice. Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into pans. Bake 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: christmas eve soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients (do not drain vegetables).
Simmer 1 to 2 hours. Serve with sliced avocado, grated cheese, chips and sour cream, if desired.

title: southern smothered green beans
directions: Cook bacon, drain, save some fat and saute onion.
Combine beans with 1/2 bacon, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook in crock-pot on low for 5 hours.
Add vinegar, sugar and bacon the last hour.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: You will need 9 1/2-inch baking pan.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash apples and remove stems.
Place popsickle sticks through center of apples.
Set aside.
In saucepan combine sugar, syrup, cream and butter.
Do not stir.
Cook to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, stir lightly.
Dip apples in syrup, remove and spin around to slightly cool the caramel.
Roll in chopped nuts if desired.
Place on waxed paper.

title: tortilla soup(from mansion on turtle creek, dallas)
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Saute 4 coarsely chopped tortillas with garlic and epazote over medium heat until tortillas are soft.
Add onion and fresh tomato purees; bring to a boil.
Add cumin, chili powder, bay leaves, canned tomato puree and chicken stock; bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat to a simmer. Add salt and cayenne pepper to taste; cook, stirring frequently, 30 minutes.
Skim fat from surface if necessary.
Strain and pour into warm soup bowls.
Garnish each with an equal portion of chicken breast, avocado, shredded cheese and crisp tortilla strips.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and eggs.
Add mixture to potatoes.
Add eggs, diced, and toss gently.

title: chicken wings
directions: Bake chicken until done.
In separate bowl, mix bottle of soy sauce and pancake syrup.
Drain chicken and add mix.
Sprinkle garlic powder on top.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until dark brown.
They should be stirred regularly until cooked.

title: dolly parton's cowboy pork and beans(celebrity recipe)
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and pepper in a 10-inch skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook string beans until almost done.
Drain; leave about 1/4 cup liquid in the pot.
Add mushroom soup; mix together.
Put 1/2 beans in casserole dish.
Add in layers:
water chestnuts, mushrooms and almonds.
Spread rest of beans on top.
Melt 2/3 stick butter; mix with 1 cup bread crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture on top.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter (optional).
Put in a 350° oven until soup is bubbling and bread crumbs are browned (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: frozen dumplings
directions: Mix shortening and egg together. Add enough plain flour to make about 4 cups of dough; roll out on floured board or counter top, cut strips and layer on plastic wrap and freeze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil (2 inches deep) to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by round teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time for about 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: pineapple daiquiri mocktail
directions: To a blender, add all ingredients.
Blend until slushy.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine shortening in flour mixture until it resembles corn meal, then pour in all at once egg mixture.
Stir until just blended, then fold in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into buttered pans and bake until done at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Let dressing stand at least 2 hours.

title: animal crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grind oatmeal in blender until fine like a powder.
Put in a large mixing bowl.
Add honey, salt, flour and soda and stir.
Cut in butter.
Add buttermilk and stir until a well-mixed dough ball forms.

title: queen's salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetarian scallop casserole
directions: Saute the vegetables while chopping or dicing the scallops. Mix all of the ingredients, including the mushroom soup.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Put 1/2 batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels over double boiler.
Add milk and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour over baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour rest of cake mix over top and return to oven.
Bake for 20 more minutes.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: sausage and pineapple
directions: Blend all ingredients except sausage and pineapple over heat until smooth.
Cut sausage into thirds and heat through.
Add sausage and pineapple to sauce.
Keep hot in fondue pot for appetizer.

title: no-fat almond fruit dessert
directions: Put fruit in a pan with 6 tablespoons sugar and the water. Cook until fruit is soft.
Put almonds in blender with 2/3 cup sugar and ground fine.

title: sour cream spinach
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Mix 3 ingredients.
Use more or less, as you wish.
(The jelly and chili sauce should be equal portions.)
Pour over chicken or any meat for sweet honeyed barbecue.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, onion and salad dressing.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon pieces and decorate with olives.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, and butter.
Pour into crust and bake until done at 275 degrees.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Lay about 40 soda crackers on sheet (or enough to cover sheet).
Boil butter and sugar mixture for about 2 minutes. Spread over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Put the chocolate chips over top when you take crackers from the oven. When they soften, they can be smoothed out and then sprinkle crushed walnuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together 2 eggs, white sugar, vanilla, salt, soda and shortening. Add water, flour and cinnamon. Beat mixture well. Stir in apples and nuts; mix. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool.

title: rice o'brien
directions: Cook rice in seasoned water for about 15 minutes (water and bouillon cubes), covered. Heat butter in skillet; saut the onions and green peppers until tender-crisp. Add the cooked rice. Fork toss with pimentos and olives.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core the cabbage and place in a big pot with water.
Boil. Lower heat; simmer and cook for 5 minutes or until leaves are pliable.
Remove from water.
Separate leaves, reserve some small ones.
In a bowl combine meat, rice, onion, green pepper, parsley, can of tomato soup, black pepper and salt.
Fill each leaf with about 3 to 4 tablespoons of mixture and fold envelope style.
Fold from bottom and fold sides in.
Shred reserved cabbage and place in cooking pot with sauerkraut.
Place cabbage rolls on top of this mixture.
Cover with crushed tomatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delightful fruit salad
directions: Chop and coat apples with lemon juice.
Mix in the grapes, oranges, marshmallows and nuts.
Combine sugar and whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold these together and chill.

title: poteca dessert bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, stir in milk, sugar, salt, egg and shortening. Mix in flour until dough is easy to handle.
Turn out on lightly floured board. Let stand 10 minutes.

Knead until smooth and elastic. Round up in a greased bowl.Cover with a damp cloth and let rise at 85° until doubled in size. Usually takes about 2 hours. Then punch down and round up again. Let rest 15 minutes.

Mix filling ingredients. Roll out dough at least to 20 inches x 30 inches. Spread with filling. Roll up. Cut into loaves. Put in greased pans. Let rise 1 hour at 85° (no longer than 1 hour). Put in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Use cream cheese frosting.

title: ange's banana-nut cake
directions: Slice bananas in large bowl, mashed.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: tabbouli salad
directions: Soak bulgur in boiling water for one hour.
Drain well.
Add other ingredients.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients and form into balls.
Dip in mixture of melted chocolate and wax.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add oil and salt.
Add flour and beat rapidly, over low heat, until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth, compact ball.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Beat hard after each until mixture is shiny and smooth.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 6 dozen.
At Christmas, these are nice with red and green gumdrops.

title: 2 meat pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper both roasts.
Roll both roasts in flour to coat.
Brown in oil in roasting pan or large Dutch oven.
Remove roasts.
Make gravy in pan using flour, soup mix and beef broth. Return roasts to pan; cover and cook in oven at 300° until done. If gravy becomes too thick, you may thin with water.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook Ramen noodles until soft, then add everything else.
Stir until blended, then serve.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Halve chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with salt and nutmeg.
Brown in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms and wine.
Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter.
Bring pan juices to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons of wine and stir into juices until thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: barnstorm coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt, lemon juice, vinegar and dill. Pour over cabbage in large bowl.
Mix to incorporate well. 8 servings.

title: layered fish dish
directions: Mix the bread crumbs, carrot, celery, parsley and onion. Place half the fillets in a greased casserole and half the crumbs mixture.
Repeat layers and dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate surprise cup cakes
directions: Prepare mix according to instructions.
Pour into muffin pans 2/3 full.
cream sugar and cream cheese;
add eggs and salt.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop by spoonfuls in center of each cup cake.
Bake as directed.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Soak rice in cool water but do not cook.
In a large saucepan, boil cabbage until leaves are tender and let cool.
Separate leaves and set aside.

title: chicken and seafood skillet
directions: Dump everything but vermicelli in skillet and cook for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one large or two small cake loaf pans.
Mix the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and grated zucchini.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder, soda and baking cocoa.
Add this mixture to previously mixed egg mixture.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until bread bounces back when touched lightly.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill 2 hours; shape into walnut size balls.
Brown the meat balls in 2 tablespoons shortening and remove.
Blend flour, salt and water, cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Add meat balls and heat well.
Stir in sour cream.

title: joberta's sweet pickles
directions: Place sliced or cubed cucumbers in brine of salt and water. Let stand 6 days.
Stir well each day.
On the last day, drain and wash thoroughly in clear water.
Add water to cover and alum.
Boil 10 minutes and drain.
Add clear water to cover and ginger.
Boil 10 minutes and drain.
Add 1 quart vinegar and 1 pint water, sugar, celery seed, whole cloves and 1 stick cinnamon.
Boil until clear. Put into jars and seal.
Take cinnamon out as you fill jars.
May add green food coloring to desired color.

title: quiche
directions: Melt butter; saute onions.
Place ham, onion, grated cheese, pimento and chives in pie crust; slightly mix.
Stir eggs, milk, seasoning and flour until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coffee hermits (cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and cold coffee.
Dissolve soda in hot coffee.
Mix alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Soften cream cheese and butter.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sunday nite cube steak
directions: Flour steak and brown on both sides.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drain mushrooms, reserve liquid.
Add enough water to the liquid to make 1 cup.
On top of steak, sprinkle soup mix, mushrooms and onions.
Then pour on the juice and gravy. Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Feeds 4 to 6 people.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat all together and pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crab spread
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons water and add to soup; stir well.
Add cream cheese, blend and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into oiled mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from mold and serve with crackers.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine oats with soda. Stir into mixture.
Add M&M's and chips.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs and margarine. Set aside. Mix all other ingredients. Put half of corn flake mixture on bottom of casserole dish. Put cabbage over this. Top with remaining corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes a lot.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix milk and pudding with hand mixer until thickened.
Add the Cool Whip and set aside.
Line bottom of 9x13 pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and pour the remaining pudding over them.
Add a top layer of graham crackers.
Warm up the chocolate icing and pour over top.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter. Pat in large casserole dish. Mix well. Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sweet blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Now fold in the blueberries. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: beef and barley stuffed peppers
directions: In large saucepan or kettle, cook pepper halves in a large amount of boiling salted water 3 to 5 minutes or until tender. Drain.
In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion 5 minutes or until beef is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in barley, salsa, carrot and cumin; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese; toss to mix. Spoon mixture into pepper halves.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese atop peppers.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: bouillabaise
directions: Melt butter in 6 quart pot.
Add olive, leek, onion, bay leaf, garlic and thyme and saute until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, clam juice, wine, Pernod and saffron.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour, being careful not to overcook.
Add clams; cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add scallops and fish; cover and cook for 10 minutes more until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: dream whip dessert
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Add the oleo and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pat out in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: "mexican chicken fajitas"
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni until done.
Add chicken.
Stir well.
Set aside (covered).
Take large flat pan, spray with Pam.
Heat both sides of taco shells.
Add chicken mixture, then taco or Cheddar cheese (in package).
Roll and serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour and sugar; mix. Beat egg and add to flour and sugar mixture. Add vinegar and reserved pineapple juice.
Cook and stir in 1 1/2 or 2-quart saucepan on low heat until thick, 3 to 5 minutes. Cool.

title: chipped beef bake
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream together; mix well.
Add onion, garlic and beef; mix well.
Put in crock-pot on low.
Cook until hot.
Serve warm with crackers or rye rounds.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: In heavy skillet, brown chicken in butter or margarine; remove chicken, add onion and garlic to skillet and saute until lightly browned.
Add a dash of salt and remaining ingredients (except pepper).
Return chicken to skillet, spoon sauce over all.
Cover, simmer 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
*I use chicken bouillon granules.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine cooked sweet potatoes, butter and eggs.
Mix well. Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to potato mixture.
Mix well. Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add to potato mixture.
Mix well. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.
Happy eating!

title: gene's potatoes
directions: Follow directions for 6 cups instant potatoes.
Do not make them soupy; may want to cut back on water or milk just a little. When they are prepared according to package directions, add sour cream, cream cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Whip the sin out of them.
May add shredded cheese, chives, parsley, bacon bits or whatever seasoning you may like.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or a little longer if they have been refrigerated prior to baking.

title: good enough to be called dessert, salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Combine canned juice, retained juice and water to make 2 cups. Add to hot mixture. Refrigerate until partially congealed. Fold in Cool Whip. Combine with jello mixture and refrigerate in 9 x 13 dish.

title: cranberry-oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven
Combine oat bran, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and	brown sugar in a mixing bowl;
blend with a fork. Beat
egg
whites,	milk,
oil,
vanilla, chopped cranberries and apple
concentrate in a separate bowl with a fork. Add liquid mixture to dry and stir until blended.
Fill muffin tins.
Place in oven.
Lower temperature to 400°.
Bake for 17 to 20
minutes. Cool
slightly
before
removing
from
tins. Makes 12.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together and spoon over lettuce leaf.

title: copper pennies
directions: In pan, place all ingredients except carrots and bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the cooked carrots.
Put in refrigerator and chill overnight.
Will keep for a long time.
The longer it sets the better it is.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Put jar of tomatoes in a 6-quart pot.
Add eggplant, green pepper, red pepper, onion, zucchini and garlic and simmer 60 minutes on the stove.
Or, use a microwavable 4-quart casserole dish and cook 30 minutes at Medium (50%), stirring every 2 minutes.
When you take out of microwave, let sauce sit for 2 minutes and then pour over spaghetti or pasta of choice.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients to make meatballs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
In saucepan, combine next 6 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Microwave spread in a large microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with spread.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 40 seconds. Immediately add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Press into a baking pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 24.

title: brisket
directions: Trim fat off brisket.
Liberally sprinkle meat tenderizer and garlic salt on both sides of brisket.
Pour Worcestershire sauce and rub in with hands on both sides, then rub in brown sugar on both sides with hands.
Bake in oven at 250° in covered pan for 7 or 8 hours (I usually bake it overnight) or until tender.

title: glorified rice
directions: *May need to add more Cool Whip to keep fluffy.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Place peeled banana, milk and ice cream or yogurt into a blender and blend until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in tube pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package and cool.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: spaghetti saporiti
directions: Mince onion, celery, parsley, rosemary, sage and anchovies together.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Brown and stir with wooden spoon.
Dilute tomatoes with wine; add to mixture.
Add salt and pepper (not too much salt, as anchovies are salty).
Reduce heat to moderate; let the sauce simmer.
Cook spaghetti in salted water until al dente (firm to bite).
Drain; turn onto a warm serving dish.
Mix the sauce and grated cheese with the spaghetti and serve.
(Serves 4 to 6.)

title: golden state salad
directions: In large bowl, mix yogurt, orange juice concentrate, honey and salt to blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce and sunflower nuts.
Toss to coat.
Line bowl or individual plates with lettuce leaves.
Fill with fruit mixture. Sprinkle with sunflower nuts.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, celery and bell pepper and English peas in oblong dish.
Add a layer of mayonnaise; spread out.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Add layer of grated cheese and layer of Bac*Os.
Make several hours in advance or overnight.

title: white cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add egg whites one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in two 9-inch round pans lined with waxed paper, greased and floured.
Ice with One Minute Chocolate Icing.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all but mayonnaise. If you wish, you may use Italian dressing.

title: nana's ginger cookies
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda, cloves, ginger and sugar. Cream Crisco and margarine. When fluffy, add eggs (one at a time). Mix in molasses and dry ingredients. Drop in small lumps on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool before removing from the pan. These are very crisp. Makes 6 dozen.

title: outrageous cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oleo, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla. Add flour and baking soda and mix well.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cookies will be soft.
Do not overbake.

title: pecan brittle(low-fat)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water; cook slowly until sugar dissolves and mixture forms a soft ball (236°), 15 to 20 minutes. Add pecans and salt; cook until mixture hardens slightly (295°), 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Stir.
Pour evenly into well-greased, shallow pan.
Cool partially.
Turn when firm.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: lasagne
directions: To make meat sauce, combine ground beef, Ragu, tomato juice, salt and oregano; simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg together.
Add nuts, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add potato chips.
Roll into small balls. Dip
fork
in
sugar
to flatten balls a little.
Bake until golden brown at 375° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken and 2 teaspoons salt in water until tender.
Bone and cut in pieces and save 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth.
Combine soup, tomatoes, chicken broth and 1/2 teaspoon salt in small saucepan and heat.
Layer chicken, tortillas (that have been cut in 1/2-inch strips), cheese, chopped onion and heated sauce in an electric skillet.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cook at 250° for 20 minutes, then 200° for 40 minutes.
Can layer in pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Put into a 3-quart casserole dish. Add seasoning, parsley, black pepper, garlic, tomatoes (poke holes in tomatoes) and tomato sauce.
Mix.
Put into a 350° oven for 1 hour. Slice bell peppers and mushrooms. Add to casserole and return to oven until peppers are tender, not soggy.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Follow the pound cake recipe directions on the back of the cake mix box.
Butter and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan; pour batter into the pan.
Place sliced peaches over the top; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake as directed for pound cake.
About 10 minutes before it is finished, coat top with butter and more cinnamon and sugar.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Strain the spices from the cider and pour into serving mugs.
Serves 8.

title: easy eclair dessert
directions: Arrange half of the crackers on the bottom of a 13 x 9 baking pan, breaking crackers, if necessary, to fit.
Pour milk into a large bowl and add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Place half of the remaining crackers over pudding; top with remaining pudding mixture and crackers.
Remove top and foil from frosting and microwave on high 1 minutes or until pourable. Spread evenly over crackers.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Cut into squares to serve.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips and place in an ungreased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: microwave chili
directions: Combine onion and green pepper in a 5-quart casserole or bowl. Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave on Medium (50%) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.
