Serves 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine Karo and sugar in pan.
Heat over medium heat until sugar is dissolved (10 minutes), stirring often.
Add peanuts and salt.
Heat over medium-high heat until nuts are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour baking soda.
(Hold on to your seat!
Will boil up.
Stir fast!)
When it simmers down, pour mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add margarine and 2 cups cheese; stir until melted, then add 1 can milk.
Beat eggs and add 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Stir and then add 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Cook 3 hours on low in crock-pot.
Don't lift lid.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together sour cream, softened cream cheese and taco seasoning mix.
Spread mixture in bottom of large casserole dish (approximately 9 x 9-inches).
Pour taco sauce over mixture. Brown ground beef and crumble over sauce.
Top with lettuce, tomato, cheese, onion and hot peppers, if desired.
Chill for few hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: southwestern cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir chips and margarine in small bowl; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Beat cream cheese and eggs in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Mix in shredded cheese and chilies; pour over crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream over cheesecake.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Refrigerate.
Top with remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: bacon-n-scallops dip
directions: Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Serve as dip for scallops.
Cook bacon 8 minutes at 350° in a pizza pan.
Take out and wrap strips around scallops.
Put back on pizza pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add pecan halves and cook 20 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix sugar and spices together in a paper bag.
Add warm nuts and shake to coat.

title: uncle hammy's chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Shake together.
Can marinate chicken overnight for extra flavor.
Baste chicken as it cooks.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together and fry in deep fat.
Great with honey and fish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dad's brown bread
directions: Cream sugar, molasses and eggs together.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Mix softened ingredients and refreeze.
To serve, mix 2 tablespoons mix with 1 cup boiling water.
Add rum to taste. Sprinkle with dash of nutmeg.

title: one-step lasagne(actually, it's three steps.)
directions: Don't be afraid to tackle lasagne just because you are a beginner.

This recipe was designed for you, which eliminates cooking the noodles beforehand, which most people find the most tedious job of all (the noodles have a tendency to tear unless you cook them perfectly; they also love to slip into the sink when you are trying to drain them).

title: suckling pig(prosie pieczone)
directions: Clean pig and wash well inside and out with clear water.
Rub well with salt. Sprinkle with white pepper inside and out. Stuff the cavity with dressing and sew up with linen thread or white cord.
Cover ears and tail with pieces of well-greased paper. Place in roaster.
Brush with a little fat and roast at 375° for 2 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes. Pig's mouth should be open and a potato inserted.
After roasting, remove the potato and place an apple in the mouth.
If you want the skin of the pig to be soft, baste with hot stock; if you want it to be crusty, baste with oil or melted butter. Remove hot pig to hot platter and garnish with parsley or watercress.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In 3-quart casserole, cook bacon on high 1 1/2 to 3 minutes until crisp.
Add celery, onions and potatoes.
Cook on high 7 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.
If using olive or salad oil, cook with vegetables.
Meanwhile, drain clams reserving liquid and add water if needed, to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add clam liquid, potatoes, tomatoes with their liquid, salt, thyme and pepper to casserole.
Cook, covered, on high 18 to 25 minutes, until potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Add reserved clams.
Cook, covered, on high 2 to 3 minutes until clams are heated through.
Makes 8 cups, about 125 calories per cup.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil water and sugar 10 minutes; cool.
Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water and let cool.
Mix together with rest of ingredients and freeze 24 hours.
To serve, place 1 ice cream scoop of slush into serving glass and fill with Seven-Up.

title: french meat pie
directions: Put everything in a pint saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Cook one potato, smash it and add to mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake until lightly brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs (venison)
directions: Combine venison, onion, celery, bread crumbs and eggs to make meatballs.
Place in deep-sided baking dish.
In bowl, mix cranberry sauce, sauerkraut and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; pick off bone and set aside.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In a greased baking dish or pan, put a layer of dressing mix, then put a layer of chicken, then pour soup (diluted with broth) over chicken.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° until brown (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: candy caroline
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Drop on wax paper, then eat!
Eat! Eat!

title: chicken dinner in a dish(microwave)
directions: Wash chicken legs; pat dry.
Combine crumbs, garlic salt and paprika on waxed paper.
Dip chicken in milk; roll chicken in crumbs to coat evenly.
Arrange chicken on one side of a divided dish.
Place potatoes to each end of the other section of divided dish.
Add peas to center (between potatoes).
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on full power 6 to 7 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Once browned, add Lawry's taco seasoning and Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix. Mix together thoroughly.
Add stewed tomatoes, Ro-Tel, corn and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer.
Serve over Fritos.
Top with cheese.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice until it boils.
Pour over Jell-O and mix well.
Add cream cheese; mix with mixer until well blended.

title: carolina brunswick stew
directions: Bring chicken and water to boiling in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is very tender.
Skim fat from surface or chill broth and remove fat from broth.
Cool chicken to remove meat from skin and bones.
Put meat in broth along with tomatoes, potatoes, onion, pork, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add beans and corn; simmer 15 minutes. Stir in butter and Worcestershire.
Serves 8 or more.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Melt margarine.
Grate cheese.
Add these ingredients to flour, Special K and pepper.
Work well.
Knead like dough. Pinch off balls the size of a marble.
Press out on palm of hand. Lift off with knife or spatula.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until browned.
(Not good unless they are browned.)

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Add to hot water to taste.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until well mixed. Add beaten eggs and oil until well mixed. Do not beat. Add vanilla, pineapple, chopped pecans and bananas and stir until well mixed. Spoon into greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool then ice as follows:

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with one package of dry dressing mix. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until browned. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: french puffs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; stir in milk.
Put in muffin pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool a few minutes.
Dip tops and sides of muffin in melted butter, then roll them in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Makes 12.

title: cowboy cake
directions: In bowl, mix sugar and flour; set aside.
In kettle, mix cocoa, butter and water; heat to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla; mix with beater.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Prepare topping about 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° until done and golden brown.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: To browned hamburger, add Italian seasoning, garlic salt, minced onion, salt and pepper to taste and Ragu spaghetti sauce. Simmer about 15 minutes or until seasonings are well blended. Layer sauce and spaghetti noodles in large baking dish with cover, starting with sauce first.
Layer like this:
hamburger sauce, spaghetti noodles, pepperoni spaced on top, sprinkle of Mozzarella cheese, more sauce, noodles, etc.
You should end with Mozzarella on top.
Bake, covered in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: crunch cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, margarine, oil, egg, salt and vanilla.
Add baking soda, cream of tartar and flour; mix well. Add Rice Krispies, coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt, raisins and oleo.
Place in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Set aside to cool. Combine dry ingredients with cooled mixture. Turn into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Mix the remaining ingredients; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add meat balls.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally. Serve in chafing dish with picks.

title: katie's easy apple coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix and eggs together well.
Stir in apple pie filling.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and cinnamon together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: suman(filipino sweet rice cake)
directions: In large pot,
boil coconut milk and sugar for about 25 minutes (should become like syrup).
Transfer cooked rice into pot and mix until
rice
is
well
coated.
Cook
for 10 to 15 minutes; keep stirring.
Place
rice
mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wilted banana leaves or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut with plastic knife.

title: chipmunk bars or cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let cool.
Measure flour (sifted), cocoa, soda and salt and sift together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Then add flour alternately with date mixture, blending after each addition.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine Bisquick, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley flakes. Beat together eggs and oil.
Add to dry mixture.
Add zucchini and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Break 2 eggs in a one cup measuring cup and fill with milk. Stir well.
Cook 1 cup quick grits with salt; add margarine and stir well.
Add cheese and garlic powder.
Add to milk/egg mixture. Mix. Bake in buttered casserole for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: easy jalapeno cheese corn muffins
directions: Prepare mix according to directions. Stir in jalapenos, onion and cheese. Bake according to box directions.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: In covered jar or shaker, combine ingredients; chill.
Shake well before serving.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: chicken salad ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, then mix cream cheese, chicken, onions and sauce in bowl.
Shape into a ball and top with green peppers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Wash berries before hulling; save a few for garnishing.
Put 1/2 of berries in saucepan; crush.
Add sugar.
Combine cornstarch and lemon juice; add to mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and transparent in color.
Add softened gelatin and stir briskly. Cool.
Add remaining berries; stir gently.
Spoon into pie shell. Cool.
Just before serving, add whipped cream or topping.
Spread. Garnish.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
While standing, make syrup of vinegar, water and sugar.
Add celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to full boil for one minute.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Squeeze water from cabbage; add carrots and pepper, then add syrup.
Ready to freeze.

title: hawaiian ribs in a crock-pot
directions: Combine all ingredients except spareribs in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Arrange sauce and spareribs in layers in crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except herb stuffing and put in long dish.
Sprinkle top with herb stuffing and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbling.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with graham crackers.
Mix pudding by directions on box.
Mix in 16 ounces Cool Whip.
Place another layer of crackers on top of pudding.
Pour chocolate syrup over mixture.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).

title: southwest scallopini
directions: Combine flour, chili powder, cinnamon and white pepper on plate.
Dredge each turkey slice in flour mixture; gently shake off excess.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in large skillet over medium high heat.
Add as many slices of turkey as will fit in skillet without crowding.
Cook until lightly browned.
Turn over; repeat.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.
Repeat with remaining turkey, adding more butter to skillet as needed.
When all the turkey is browned, add green onions and garlic to pan drippings; cook 2 minutes.
Add orange juice, chicken broth, raisins, stirring to scrape up browned bits from bottom of pan.
Bring to a boil. Turn off heat; add the remaining butter (about 2 tablespoons) and stir until completely blended.
Pour sauce over turkey; sprinkle with almonds.
Serve with rice and mint-roasted onions.
Serves 6.

title: baked liver
directions: Place onion slices in bottom of shallow pan.
Cover with melted butter and water.
Put liver slices on onions; lay bacon strips over liver.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more, or until bacon is browned.

title: apple-grape juice
directions: Run through your juicer all ingredients.
Drink at once. Serves 1.

title: forty-niners cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease an 8-inch pie pan.
Spread cranberries on bottom. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and nuts over.
Beat egg; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat again and add rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing after cool.

title: ham-vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomatoes and milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in ham and vegetables.
Turn into a 13 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and place in a loaf pan and bake 30-40 minutes at 350° degrees.
You could substitute 2 cans (7 oz. each) tuna fish.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Brown the salted chops in oil.
Cover with rice.
Combine soup and milk and pour over rice, making sure all rice is moistened. Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 10-inch Bundt cake pan.
At low speed, beat cake mix, eggs and oil for 30 seconds. Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter evenly into Bundt pan.
Place in oven and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: buffalo chicken lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a large skillet with Pam cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken and saut 4 minutes; drain well.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, hot sauce, vinegar and garlic salt.

title: filled christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; stir in egg.
Combine milk and vanilla; set aside.
Combine flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture and mixing well after each addition.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the sugar and cranberries and let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve lemon or orange jello into hot water.
Congeal, then fold into this the cranberry mixture, nuts, marshmallows, celery and pineapple. Pour into mold.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of pan.
Drain pineapple.
Spread over filling.
Pour yellow cake mix on top.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over everything.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce and water.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add onion and saute.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, add uncooked rice.
Over this pour the consomme and bouillon.
Stir in onion and butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or longer.
Uncover last few minutes for rice to brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 9-inch casserole.
Layer zucchini, tomatoes on top of butter, salt, pepper and oregano.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend well.
Add beaten eggs, then hot applesauce.
Rub raisins and nuts with flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 325° oven.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan.
Line with wax paper.

title: beef and beans round-up
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans; heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; cut each in half.
Place biscuits cut side down over hot meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: denise's cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add other ingredients.
Let simmer approximately 1/2 hour.

title: sweet-sour curried chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Roll pieces in sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for one hour.
If using boned and skinned chicken breasts, allow 45 minutes baking time.
I serve this with rice as the sauce is delicious.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes (after baked) and slice into 1/2-inch slices. Place in casserole dish. Pour Ranch dressing over potatoes and toss to coat. Sprinkle cheese over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: peanut butter ice cream(8 quarts)
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; beat well. Add peanut butter; beat smooth. Add canned milk a little at a time.
Then add whole milk to fill can a little over half full.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown ground beef and drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of each the meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2 quart casserole dish. Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. To serve, top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes if desired.

title: herbed sweet potato biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, lemon peel, soda, basil, thyme and salt.
Combine egg, potatoes, onions, sour cream and margarine; add to the dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened. On floured surface, put dough into an 8-inch square.
Cut dough in half; cut each half crosswise into 8 strips.
Place strips on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with additional melted margarine. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegies, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Cook covered in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Cook uncovered on High 1 minute or until cheese melts.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan with the nuts.
Break 1 loaf of bread into small balls and put into pan.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, butter, milk and pudding mix in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over bread in baking pan.
Break remaining loaf of bread into small balls and put on top of mixture in pan.

title: syrup candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 20 minutes, then add last 3.
Let stand until cool enough to pull.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Blend well and refrigerate. This sauce is to be served with chicken.

title: cheese pigs in blankets
directions: Roll biscuits out and spread mustard on it.
Then you put a slice of cheese on it.
Take your hot dog and put holes in it with a fork.
Place hot dog on biscuit and roll.
Put on a lightly greased pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Gel the jello and mix together with all the other ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: shrimply delicious cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until tender; drain.
Heat soup, stir in sour cream.
Don't boil.
Season to taste.
Place flowerettes in dish, pour on sauce, sprinkle with almonds and parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Makes approximately 2 pies.
Cook pumpkin and whip well in the mixer.
Take
beaters
out	and rinse.
Replace and add sugar and butter, beat until smooth.	Add eggs, one at a time. Add milk. Add
rest of ingredients.
Beat 1 minute until well mixed.	Bake in uncooked
shell	at
for 45 minutes to 1 hour on a cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and place on a rack until cold.

title: low-fat corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl beat together egg substitute, milk and melted margarine.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until batter is smooth.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix well, adding mayonnaise.
Chill before serving.

title: blueberry jam(diet)
directions: Cut corn tortillas into 6 triangles.
Top with green chilies and a little grated part skim milk Mozzarella cheese.
Place in a 350° oven to crisp tortilla and melt cheese.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add soft butter and work into crumbs. Remove 1 cup and reserve for top.
To remainder of crumbs, add 2 teaspoons of baking powder, 2 well beaten eggs and the milk.
Stir to blend.
Place in two 9-inch layer or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan(s).
Place berries on top and sprinkle with reserved 1 cup of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: biscuits(kid's stuff)
directions: Dump all ingredients together.
Mix with hands.
When smooth, dump onto counter.
Roll dough out flat with rolling pin.
Take biscuit cutter and cut out biscuits.
Do this until all dough is gone.
Put the biscuits in a pan and put in the oven.
Bake for 5 minutes at 250°.
Serve with butter, syrup or ham!!

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into wedges.
Combine sugars, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll out half of pastry dough.
Fit into 9-inch pie pan.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, adding oatmeal last.
Form into small cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All. Add soup, mayonnaise, celery and onions.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs and sprinkle with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: alabama chicken
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Cook onions, green pepper and celery in oleo.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until blended.
Add olives and mushrooms to cheese mix.
Blend gently with mushroom soup.
Add a little chicken broth.
Boil noodles in chicken broth and drain. Add to sauce.
Fold in gently.
Bake in 9 x 15-inch greased dish. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at	300°
for
1 to 1 1/2 hours until golden brown.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: tomato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend well and make smooth. Add flour until you can't
knead anymore.
Knead about 10 minutes.

title: summer scramble
directions: Cook macaroni. Scramble ground beef, pepper and onion in skillet.

When cooked, add tomatoes and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add squash and seasonings. Steam for approximately 5 minutes or until tender. Add macaroni. If making casserole, alternate mixture with layers of shredded cheese and top with bread crumbs. Bake until cheese is melted and bread crumbs toasted. Tomato juice may be used if mixture becomes too dry. May be cooked in skillet without layering. Add any of your favorite vegetables (snow peas, green beans, etc.).

title: no-cook boiled custard
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator until you are ready to drink.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Butter both sides of bread.
Layer bottom of 3-quart Pyrex or baking with 8 buttered slices. Sprinkle half of the grated cheese over this.
Repeat with another layer of bread and cheese.
Slightly beat eggs, salt and mustard. Add milk and mix.
Pour over the bread and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight or 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.
Sometimes it takes a little longer.
Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: meatballs bourguignon
directions: In medium bowl, mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, pepper, egg, and salt.
Shape mixture into one-inch meatballs.
Cook bacon in frying pan over medium heat.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
In bacon fat, cook meatballs over medium heat until brown.
Remove meatballs and put into a bowl.
Add onions to drippings and cook until lightly brown.
Stir in water, mushrooms, carrot, and thyme. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooking wine to meatballs and half of the cooked bacon, and heat to boiling over high heat.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
In a small bowl, mix butter and flour with a spoon until well blended.
Add flour mixture to simmering liquid, stirring until mixture thickens. Remove from pan to serving dish and sprinkle remaining bacon to top.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown sausage and then hamburg and onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 2 hours on high and then on low until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin and add remaining ingredients.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each chocolate piece; cover completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set. Cool slightly.
Place on wire rack.
Cool completely.
Drizzle topping over each cookie.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix together flour and 2 teaspoons brown sugar.
With a fork or pastry blender, cut in 1/2 cup butter or margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat into ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes. In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked layer and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: microwave meat loaf and gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients well except onion soup mix.
Save this for later.
Make meat mixture into a loaf.
Place in a deep microwave casserole dish and microwave for 16 minutes on High.
Mix onion soup mix as directions say on package.
Pour over meat loaf and return to microwave and bake for 3 to 4 more minutes.
Good with mashed potatoes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper, just before completely browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for at least 1/2 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs piccalilli
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
In bowl, mix together meat, egg, bread (softened in milk) and seasonings.
Shape in 1-inch balls and saute at medium heat until evenly browned on all sides.

title: white cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix eggs, milk and lemon in another bowl.
Combine both and mix.
Do not over handle dough.
Roll into balls.
Place on tray and bake at 375° until slightly browned, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix as you would any pound cake; set oven at 325° and cook 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: rice romano
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low; cover pan and simmer about 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Place coffee and rum in saucepan and heat to a simmer.
Add the chocolate and butter.
Cook, stirring occasionally until both are melted.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is thick.
Beat in vanilla and the chocolate mixture.
Turn batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Transfer to rack to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the 1 cup pecans.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball over the remaining nuts until coated.
Chill. Let set 24 hours before serving.
Set out an hour or so before serving.
Great on Triscuits.
Keeps well.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cut fine the onion and celery and brown in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Mix all ingredients and put in buttered baking dish. Top with 3 pieces of bread, buttered and cubed.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Add 8 ounces Cool Whip. Beat until thick. In 13 x 9 dish, layer crackers. Add half of the pudding. Repeat, ending with crackers. Refrigerate for awhile.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and saute onion, garlic and curry until onions are soft.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and cream.
Stir over low heat constantly until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.

title: dream pie
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup of boiling water.
Instead of one cup of cold water, stir in 1 pint of ice cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: amaretto souffle
directions: On a cookie sheet, crumble macaroons and bake at 250° for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.
In bowl, beat 6 egg yolks, 2 eggs and sugar on high for 6 or 7 minutes.
Mixture should be frothy.
Continue beating and add Amaretto.
In a separate bowl, whip cream, then fold whipped cream into the egg mixture.
Mix in by hand 3/4 of the crumbled macaroons.
Put total mixture into serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbled macaroons.
Freeze uncovered at least 8 hours or overnight.
Delicious.
Serves 10.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil in skillet; remove onions and brown beef with the garlic in skillet.
Add onions and remaining ingredients; simmer for about 2 hours, stirring often.

title: perfect sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Thoroughly blend in dry ingredients, then add your choice of mini chips, Butterfingers or nuts.
Roll into small balls of dough and press onto pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet trash
directions: Melt bark according to package directions.
Mix cereal, nuts and pretzels together.
Pour melted almond/vanilla bark over mixture.
Then pour onto wax paper to harden.
Once hardened, break into pieces.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into strips; set aside.
Saute diced onion in oil. Add cabbage, caraway seed, salt and pepper to taste, then boiling water.
Fry until desired tenderness.

title: congealed beets
directions: Drain beets.
Reserve liquid.
Mash or grate beets.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add vinegar and sugar to juice; heat to hot, but do not boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in mixture.
Add mashed beets.
Grease pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and chill well.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water.
Beat at medium speed. Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to egg mixture until moistened. Stir in potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Spoon into 2 (1 pound) coffee cans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer bottom of pan with Doritos.
Brown and drain hamburger and onions.
Add taco seasoning and follow directions.
Put on top of Doritos.
Then layer tomato sauce, sour cream, and cottage cheese.
Line edge of casserole with Doritos.
Crumble Doritos and cover top. Add cheddar cheese, and
bake at 350 degree for 1/2 hour.
325 for glass pan.

title: never fail pastry
directions: Cut shortening into the flour and salt.
Add the egg, water and vinegar; mix.
This amount will roll out for 4 or 5 crusts.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pat out in flat patties and fry in a mixture of butter and shortening.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease bottom only of two 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pans.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-cup Pyrex bowl, mix sugar and Karo. Microwave on High 4 minutes. Add peanuts. Stir and microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes, then add vanilla and butter.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Add baking soda. Stir until fluffy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Cool. Break into pieces.

title: quick dessert
directions: Fold cherry pie filling, pineapple, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip together.
Sprinkle with walnuts or pecans.
Chill well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: You can add 1 teaspoon vinegar.

title: 7-up steak
directions: Place all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bake at 250° for at least 4 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix by hand or in blender using enough milk to soften.
Serve with chips.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook water, potatoes, celery, carrots & onion until tender. Add soup, cheese and ham.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; Stir into the sugar mixture, add walnuts. Pour into a greased 9 inch square baking pan. Sprinkle topping over batter, add water, (DO NOT STIR AFTER WATER IS ADDED) and bake at 350 for 30 minutes. Allow to cool for 10 minutes. Then top with hot fudge and ice cream if desired.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color; add oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, alternately with the pumpkin, on low speed. Stir in walnuts.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Check after 1 hour.
Completely cool before removing cake from pan.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift and mix all dry ingredients, then add buttermilk and eggs, then shortening.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Grease tins well.
Makes about 20 small muffins.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Baking instructions not given.
I loved to come home from school to have a piece of cake with whipped cream.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a pan. Put on top of stove to warm. Heat enough to melt sugar. Then put into your freezer, then add milk to fill up freezer.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in casserole dish.
Pour soup over and bake covered for 1/2 an hour or until potatoes are tender at 350°.
Can also be put in crock-pot and cook on high for 6 hours.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello.
Heat over medium heat until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken, then add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until thick.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add cold water and drain.
Put in a bowl and add the diced onion, carrots, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Put 1/2 wafers in bottom of 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Cream butter and mix well with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well. Spread over wafers.
Cover with sliced berries, spread whipped cream over this.
Cover with rest of crumbs.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.

title: canned salmon
directions: For each pint of salmon mix together 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon light mustard, 1 tablespoon catsup and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Can 3 hours or pressure can 1 1/2 hours at 15 pounds pressure.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli; drain and place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add liquid slowly and stir until smooth.
Add cheese food and stir until melted.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and add eggs, one at a time, beating until well mixed.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh pumpkin pie
directions: Use a small to medium size pumpkins.
Clean and slice meat from the rind.
Cut pumpkins into squares and bake in a covered 4.5 liter (or larger) dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until pumpkin is very tender.
Remove and put immediately into a blender and make puree.

title: flip-flop cobbler
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine with 1/2 cup sugar. In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Alternately add these ingredients and milk to the creamed mixture. Spread batter in greased casserole dish or loaf pan. Top batter with fruit, and pour 1 cup of juice over the top of fruit. Top fruit with another 1/2 cup sugar. (Can omit sugar if fruit is already sweet enough to your liking.) Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Put butter and cheese into broccoli while hot and let melt.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crush 1 stack Ritz crackers from 12 ounce box. Mix with 1 stick of melted butter and spread over top of casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.
This may be made a day ahead of time but is best to fix crust on day of baking.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
Mix nuts and coconut and spread in pan.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain off fat.
Start with a layer of potatoes, then layer beef, onions, peas, corn and sliced cheese.
Repeat, ending with pouring cream chicken over top.
Place sliced cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: 30 minute chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions in skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, chili powder and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Cream together the butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add the sugar and brown sugar, creaming well. Blend in dry ingredients gradually and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on each cookie pressing down firmly so that cookie cracks around the edge. Return cookies to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Slice bananas and arrange on bottom of prepared pastry shells. Whip the Dream Whip as directed on package, then add cream cheese and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over bananas.
Top with the pie filling.
Chill until set.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: sour cream white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring until sugar melts.
Do not boil anymore, but cook slowly to 236° or to a soft ball stage.
Let stand 15 minutes, then add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss and pour into lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Score warm, then cut into squares when cooled.

title: p.e.o. bean soup
directions: Wash bean mixture and cover with water and add salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain and rinse in the morning.
Place in heavy pot with 2 quarts water, ham hock and bay leaf.
Bring to rapid boil. Place in crock-pot or continue simmering for 3 hours.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour longer and enjoy.

title: the standing rib
directions: Place meat, fat side up, in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Insert a meat thermometer. Roast in a 325° oven until:
rare, 2 1/2 hours or 140°; medium, 3 hours or 160°; or well done, 3 1/4 hours or 170°.
Cover with foil to keep warm.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: Scoop and eat with Fritos.

title: rhine lander cheese fondue
directions: Grate cheese. Bring water, wine, butter and seasoning to a boil.
Add cheese and set in double boiler or a fondue pot.
Stir until cheese melts.
If too thick, add more wine; if too thin, add more cheese. Eat with bread sticks or 2-inch squares of rye bread. Cheese will burn easily, so watch closely.

title: tostada dip
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all well.
Next, to 1 cup brown sugar, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix well.
Layer 1/2 cake mixture, then 1/2 sugar, then 1/2 cake mixture and 1/2 sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: uncooked persimmon pudding
directions: Put all ingredients, except graham crackers, into a bowl; blend well.
Sprinkle a few cracker crumbs on bottom of a 9-inch square greased pan.
Spread pudding over crumbs; garnish with more crumbs.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or milk.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Thaw raspberries.
Pour boiling water over jello.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Stir in crushed pineapple and juice. Refrigerate until starting to set around the edges.
Fold in nuts, bananas and thawed raspberries and juice.
Put in mold. Refrigerate to congeal.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Spread graham cracker squares with desired amount of peanut butter.
Carefully sprinkle candy sprinkles over peanut butter. Enjoy.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins
in
water until water is gone. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix.
Blend in other ingredients which have been sifted together. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter mochi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together milk, vanilla and eggs; then add butter.
In a separate bowl mix dry ingredients. Gradually pour dry ingredients into wet batter.
Bake for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan or until golden brown.

title: butter mints or party mints
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add food coloring and butter flavoring.
Mix until coloring all looks same shade. Shape into balls the size of marbles.
Place on foil or waxed paper and flatten with thumb.
Let dry for 1 1/2 days.
Can be frozen. Yields 100 mints.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375°.
This makes 3 dozen.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill. May be served on lettuce leaves.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Saute veggies in butter; put shrimp and soup into veggies and let simmer.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease pans.
Beat all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Mix cake mix and oleo until crumbly.
Add egg and mix well. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk over crust.
Sprinkle chips on top and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, tomatoes, onions, peppers and pimento. Soak overnight in pickling salt.
Drain but do not squeeze the water from vegetables.
Cover with vinegar; add sugar and spices. Boil slowly 20 minutes.

title: pecan pies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks together.
Add syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into pie mixture.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: pita bread
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, salt and hot water; stir to dissolve sugar and salt.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over and allow to dissolve.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead thoroughly.
Divide into 12 small pieces and roll into balls.
With rolling pin, roll each ball into 5-inch circle.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 500° for 5 to 7 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Yields 12 rounds.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix raisins with 2 cups flour, then mix all dry ingredients. Heat and mix applesauce, shortening and sugar; mix well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Mix soda with 2 1/2 cups flour.
Stir well. Combine all spices, nuts, cocoa and salt.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place cut pieces of biscuits into a greased bundt pan. Melt butter with cinnamon and sugar; pour over top of biscuit pieces. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Remove from oven and invert onto serving plate.

title: oreo freak-out
directions: Pat 20 crushed Oreos into oblong Pyrex dish. Add softened ice cream on top and smooth. Evenly spread peanuts over ice cream. Pour syrup over all.
Spread Cool Whip evenly over syrup. Sprinkle 10 crushed Oreos on top. Freeze overnight.
Let set out 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cook sausage over low heat in a large skillet 8 to 10 minutes. Drain; set aside.
Combine chili sauce and next 3 ingredients in large skillet; stir well.
Add kielbasa and pineapple chunks. Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve in chafing dish. Yields 24 appetizer servings.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Cool potatoes completely before peeling and cubing them.
Mix all ingredients together and serve cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Drain raspberries and puree in a blender.
Arrange rinsed and dried strawberries in a glass bowl, pyramid fashion.
Sprinkle with lime juice and then with granulated sugar.
Spoon raspberry puree over strawberries.
Top with whipped cream to which the powdered sugar and Kirsch have been added.
If preferred, may be served in individual bowls or stemmed glasses.

title: shake up sugar-n spice dressing
directions: Put all ingredients together in a jar; place a lid on the jar and shake.
Pour on salad before serving.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle entire box of rice on bottom. Lay chicken over the rice. In bowl, mix soup and 2 cans of water. Pour over chicken and rice. Cover with foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°. Do not peek.

title: bison roast in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place roast on ample piece of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the meat.
Bring edges of foil together.
Add water and seal tightly.
Place in shallow pan.
Reduce oven temperature and bake at 275° for 2 to 4 hours or until internal temperature reaches desired doneness.

title: beef taco rice skillet
directions: Cook beef in 10-inch skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown. Drain. Stir in seasoning mix, water, salsa and corn. Heat to boiling. Stir in rice. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 8 minutes. Fluff rice mixture with fork. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle lettuce around edge of edge. Sprinkle tomato in circle next to lettuce. Serve with sour cream.

title: cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly blend crumbs and margarine and 1/4 cup sugar. Press firmly against bottom and 2 1/2-inch up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add remaining 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend in sour cream.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 70 minutes, or until firm.
Turn off oven.
Leaving door slightly ajar, allow cheesecake to remain in oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Chill 4 hours or overnight. Remove side of pan.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 10 wedges.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is crumbly; set aside. Obtain 9-inch pie shell; set aside.
Combine 4 remaining ingredients.
Alternate layers in pie shell of crumbs and liquid mixture, ending with crumbs as top layer.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes longer or until firm.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls (small) and flatten. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, but not until brown!

title: tomato salad dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 5 or 10 minutes.
Mix milk, flour, eggs and vanilla while first mixture is heating.
After mixing separately the 2 sets of ingredients, mix all together and cook until thick (5 or 10 minutes).

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll into 58 to 60 balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix well in blender.
Dip bite size vegetables, meat, seafood and poultry pieces in this batter before frying in hot oil.
This is a fun, tabletop, cook your own food meal.
Great for onion rings, too.

title: mock pineapple
directions: Remove peel and seeds from zucchini before grating.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour zucchini mixture into hot jars, leaving 1/2 inch head space.
Process for 30 minutes in hot water bath.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes; cook in boiling water to cover 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Combine potatoes and next 8 ingredients; toss gently.
Set aside.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, mustard, pepper and red pepper. Stir well and pour over potato mixture.
Toss gently; cover and chill.

title: feijoada
directions: Soak beans and smoked meat in separate pots overnight.
Drain beans and add enough water to cook.
Add salt pork and cook 1 hour over low flame.
Cut the rest of the meats into pieces and add to the beans.
Cover and cook for another 1 1/4 hours.
Put a little oil in a skillet and saute the garlic and onion for 5 minutes. Add the tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook for another 5 minutes.
Remove 2 cups of beans and mix them in the skillet, mashing as you mix.
Add enough liquid from the beans to moisten the mixture.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes or until it becomes thick.
Scrape the sauce into the bean pot and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry-oat salad
directions: Toast oatmeal in a skillet over low heat, stirring constantly. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin-pan cups.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, blend egg, milk and oil.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries and toasted oatmeal.
Spoon batter into muffin cups and bake 20 minutes.

title: barbecued black-eyes
directions: Cook peas in boiling water with salt until peas are barely tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Pour off half of liquid. Brown ground beef and onion; add to peas.
Stir in barbecue sauce, mustard and sugar.
Bake at 200° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: country potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut each half diagonally into 1/8-inch slices, keeping potato assembled.
Lift with spatula onto oiled baking sheet.
Press down slightly with palm of hand to fan out slightly.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake for 15 to 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: five can soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for several hours.
I make mine in the slow cooker.
Very good.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in water in top of double boiler.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto buttered waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm enough to remove from paper.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Dip candy mixture a few pieces at a time into chocolate.
Place on buttered waxed paper.

title: easy broccoli souffle
directions: In blender or food processor, puree broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour in medium casserole.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven 20 minutes or until souffle is puffy and top is brown.
Serve immediately.
May sprinkle with additional grated Cheddar cheese.

title: govier family bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients up to taco seasoning.
Place in crock-pot or casserole; add cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° or heat in crock until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Then add the melted margarine.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
Excellent!

title: hot caramel sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, corn syrup, 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup cream.
Bring to boil; gradually add remaining cream and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, just to soft ball stage (230°).
Remove from heat.
Add salt and vanilla extract.
Serve warm.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch pans and dust with flour.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
In separate bowl, cream the sugar and butter, then add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, starting with dry ingredients, and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Remove butter and cheese from refrigerator about 15 minutes ahead.
Beat in small bowl of mixer until blended.
With fingertips or wooden spoon blend in flour and salt until dough is smooth.
Shape in flat mound on sheet of foil, wrap and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 to 30 minutes before rolling.
Divide in halves or quarters for ease in handling.
Wrap reserved portions and return to refrigerator.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill 30 minutes and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.

title: snack crackers
directions: Heat oil and mix, coating crackers, then add dry ingredients; mix well.

title: honey
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir together. Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Sugar and regular Italian dressing may be used.

title: sweet noodles
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add soup and 2 to 2 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles. Cook until tender. Simmer until thick. Add sugar to taste.

title: golden crescents
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape dough from side of bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour oil and buttermilk into one measuring cup; do not stir.
Pour all at once into the flour. Stir with a fork until mixture cleans sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ovenproof casserole dish, melt 1 stick of butter.
In additional bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk until smooth.
Add this to melted butter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate-chocolate-chocolate cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix and drop on biscuit sheet or in muffin tins. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix other ingredients and put in a casserole.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Place in microwave and cook until thick.
Stir often.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Refrigerate and use desired amount for fresh fruit salad.

title: chicken poppy seed casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place bite size pieces of cooked chicken into casserole (greased) dish. Combine sour cream and soup; pour over chicken. Crush crackers and mix with melted butter and poppy seed. Sprinkle on top of chicken. Bake for 30 minutes, until golden and bubbly.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix cooked broccoli and rice together.
Pour into baking dish.
Add the soup and mix well. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off and leave pie in for about 30 minutes or until set.

title: eclair cake
directions: Boil water.
Pour over margarine.
Stir until melted.
Stir in flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Pour mixture into broiler pan or large cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
It will puff up.
Pat down (while warm) and let cool. Make topping by creaming cream cheese with mixer.
Add pudding and milk.
Spread over crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: banana cake
directions: Cook in 3 cake pans in 350° oven until done.

title: honey-banana pops
directions: You will need 8 (3 ounce) paper cups and 8 wooden sticks.

title: macaroni and ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together after macaroni is boiled.
Chill and serve.
You may also serve warm.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Mix the cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Arrange stuffed shells in dish and pour remaining sauce mixed with meat over the shells. Cover baking dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle additional 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (optional) over shells.
Continue baking for additional 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, melt butter and mix all ingredients.
Place in an uncooked pie crust and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until browned on top.

title: zucchini corn fritters
directions: Mix and bake on hot griddle.

title: flemish carbonade
directions: Melt butter.
Brown meat in hot butter.
Add onions, etc.
(up to and including consomme).
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the rice in separate pot (enough for 5 to 6).
Add corn and peppers to meat and tomato mixture and continue heating for 10 minutes.
Add some of the mushroom liquid if needed.
Serve over rice.
Leftover rice should be stored separate from meat mixture so it will not absorb all the liquid.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apple slices in large bowl.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and flour together and pour over apples.
Stir until apples are well coated.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Dot with oleo.
Place top crust over apples and prick with fork.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 35 minutes more.

title: good and quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Form into cookies.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 64 cookies.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add 1/2 stick melted butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix and pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Pour 1 can sweetened fruit with 1/2 cup sugar over batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil. Mix all other ingredients and add to raisins. Cook slowly until thick. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Cover with lattice crust and bake at 325 degrees for about
45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour mixture. Then add raisins, nuts, vanilla and pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended and chill at least 2 hours.

title: napa cabbage slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, canola oil and the herb packet from the Ramen noodles.
Add chopped cabbage, water chestnuts,
onion, crushed noodles and almonds.
Refrigerate.	Looks better if served the same day but good the next day also.
Serves 8 or more.

title: blood sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into cloth casings, about 10 inches long, by 4 inches round.
Leave room for expansion.
Cook in boiling water for about 2 hours until done.
Remove from bags, slice and fry in butter.
Good with syrup and hot bread.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and spread the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
In a bowl mix the next 3 ingredients together and fold in Cool Whip until well blended. Spread this mixture over cooled crust and top with your favorite fruit.
Refrigerate and serve immediately.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute
beef,
onions,
green
pepper,
celery,
garlic, mushrooms and cheese together.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Season
with
oregano,
celery
salt,
Italian seasoning, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add cottage cheese, egg
and Parmesan cheese.
Spread in large baking pan: sauce, noodles, cheese mixture, sauce, noodles, cheese mixture and ending with sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients, other than shrimp, with mixer until dip consistency.
Do not overmix or it will become runny.
Fold in shrimp or shrimp pieces.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Place in a large greased casserole and cook for 1 hour at 350°. Cover with crushed potato chips and return to oven for 30 minutes longer.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix the red hot peppers and the salted crackers.
Add a pinch of cinnamon.
Stir-fry the ingredients.
Fry tortillas.
Dip each tortilla in the stir-fried ingredients.
Chop up onion and mix with grated cheese.
Place in center of tortilla and roll.
Place tortillas on tray and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: potato burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into patties and place on broiling pan or grill.
Broil until brown.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: In heavy 3-quart pan, melt first three ingredients and stir in peanuts until covered.
Spread on waxed paper to harden.
Break into pieces.

title: microwave scampi
directions: Combine oil and garlic in oval microproof baking dish, just large enough to accommodate all ingredients.
Cook (micro) on High for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: gelatin fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve liquid.
Combine 1 cup boiling water and lemon gelatin in mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve gelatin. Add drained pineapple and 1 cup ice cubes.
Stir until ice is melted. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and put in refrigerator to set.
Repeat with orange gelatin, using remaining water and ice.
Stir in marshmallows instead of pineapple.
Pour over lemon layer.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Cook ground beef, chopped onion and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer and pour over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Drain pineapple; save juice and pour over apples.
Add to egg mixture the Cool Whip, pineapple, drained apples and 1 2/3 cup peanuts.
Mix thoroughly. Top with remaining peanuts and refrigerate.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in hot pint jars.
Put 1 pod of pepper and 1 clove of garlic in each jar.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Blend sugar, syrup and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla appetizer wedges
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
Stir in chilies, onions and jalapenos.
Season with salt and pepper (or a little salsa for color).

Spread one tortilla with about 1/4 cup of mixture; top with another tortilla. Continue spreading and stacking until stack is 4 tortillas high; top with the 5th tortilla that has not been spread with cheese mixture.
Make another stack with the remaining 5 tortillas.
Wrap each stack in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut each stack into 18 wedges.
Arrange pinwheel fashion around a dish of salsa or picante.
Makes 36 appetizer servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat egg until frothy; beat in sugar and butter or margarine; cream until fluffy.
Add sour cream and vanilla; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to sour cream mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar topping evenly over batter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: church casserole(freda adams - bethel, ohio)
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Shape into small balls with hands.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and press down lightly with thumb.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli, water and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and sugar together with a fork.
Stir in melted shortening and beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: bob's cherry jello delight
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of jello in boiling water.
Mix in grape juice and add cherries.
Chill and enjoy.

title: he-man cocoa
directions: In a large saucepan combine cocoa, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat carefully, stirring often.
Be careful not to scorch.
Serve cocoa hot, topped with marshmallows.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, soda, salt, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake at 325°.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with a sprig of mint (optional).

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix sour cream, pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put bouillon cubes in blender first, then add onion.
Blend both very fine.
Add softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in oats.
Mix in oil, egg and milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Place in greased 9 x 13 pan. Chill 8 to 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 8 people.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Boil together the sugar, water and Karo to 300°.
Let all bubbles disappear.
Add peanut butter.
Blend well.
Pour out onto buttered foil.
Press out with back of lightly greased spatula. Cut immediately with scissors into bite size pieces.

title: bubble-up pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In batter bowl, quarter biscuits with knife. Stir in 1 cup sauce and 2 cups of cheese. Spread mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour remaining sauce and cheese over the top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: knorr's spinach dipp
directions: Stir together, then add spinach. Chill 2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa. Add butter and milk. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil; boil about 30 seconds. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Will harden as they sit.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry beef and bacon.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together and make balls about walnut size.
Chill or freeze (works best frozen).
Dip balls into melted chocolate. Super good!

title: pasta primavera
directions: Blanch vegetables except peas.
Run under cold water to maintain color after blanching.
Run hot water over frozen peas. Heat oil; add crushed garlic and saute until it turns slightly brown.
Add boiling broth carefully to hot oil and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook pasta until al dente.
Pour garlic/oil sauce over pasta.
Add vegetable and toss.
Serve at room temperature. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles by directions on package.
Drain.
Brown beef with salt, pepper, green peppers and garlic powder.
Stir in tomato sauce and oregano.
Set aside.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend with sour cream, then add cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Place half the noodles in a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cover with cheese mixture.
Spread the rest of the noodles over top. Pour on the meat sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: slovak jelly squares(paherai)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet, pat 3/4 of the dough on the bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of pan.
Spread any of your favorite jam over the dough.
Roll remaining 1/4 portion of dough on floured board, cut into thin strips and crisscross across top of jam.
If dough breaks when crossing, just patch it.
Sprinkle with 1 cup ground nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut in squares or diamonds.
Keeps well.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Heat butter or margarine in a heavy skillet over high heat. Add zucchini, onions, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese; heat until cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, onion, soup and sour cream.
Melt margarine and combine with stuffing.
Put half of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add squash and top with rest of stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free low-fat pineapple pudding
directions: In a bowl, whisk the sour cream, pineapple and pudding mix until blended and thick. Serve with vanilla wafers.

title: herb chicken bake
directions: Prepare rice.
Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown in margarine.
Spoon rice into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with chicken, skin side up.
Combine soup with wine.
Stir and heat over medium heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine in small bowl.
Mix well.
Press in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: caramel twix bars
directions: Mix the caramels with the water in saucepan and melt over low heat.
Put the cookies side by side on an ungreased cookie sheet. Spoon a dab of caramel onto each cookie.
Place pan in the refrigerator until the caramel firms up.
In a double boiler over low heat, melt the chocolate chips.
Remove pan from the refrigerator.
Rest one cookie at a time on a fork and carefully dip in the chocolate.
Place on wax paper and let cool several hours.

title: peppermint party pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press in bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Gradually add milk to Marshmallow Creme with mixer or wire whip.
Stir in vanilla and fold in Cool Whip and candy.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks are formed.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until mixture is very stiff.
Fold in nuts and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Turn into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan and make a nest-like shell, building sides up 1/2 inch above edge of pan.
Bake in slow oven of 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Place chocolate and water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Cool until thickened.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In a separate bowl, whip cream.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Spoon into meringue shell. Chill about 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Have all meats and cheeses sliced thin.
Layer 1/2 of all meats and cheeses on each pizza dough in order that they are listed.
Top meats and cheeses with a very thin layer of sauce. Fold dough around meat and pinch together.
Bake on a tray at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 Strombolis.

title: candlestick salad
directions: On salad plates, put lettuce leaf on each plate, then put one slice of pineapple on each.
Peel and cut each banana in half crosswise and cut cherries in half.
Place a banana in center of pineapple and top with cherry on each plate.
Serves 6.

title: orange popsicle cake
directions: Make orange cake mix as
on
the box; let cool and make holes in cake, using end
of wooden spoon.
Make one (3 ounce) orange Jell-O with 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into holes.

title: treasure bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add brown sugar and sugar to butter and cream.
Beat in unbeaten eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk beginning and ending with milk. Blend well after each addition.
Stir in cherries and chocolate. Turn into 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly pan or two 9 x 9-inch pans. Grease and flour bottom.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while warm and cut into squares.

title: quick and easy peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth. Beat in biscuit mix.
Spread in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Garnish with Chocolate Drizzle. Cut into bars.
Store, covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix together the mustard and vinegar; let stand overnight. Cook in top of double boiler until thick.

title: chocolate cream brownies
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to cream mix.
Stir in nuts.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Glass pan at 325°
for 35 to 40 minutes.)

title: eve's macaroni salad
directions: Dice eggs and bacon and combine with macaroni.
Add other ingredients (mayonnaise last).
Toss and chill.
Serves 16 to 20. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender until creamy.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix flour and baking powder and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in apples, raisins and oats.
Beat in egg and milk and blend.
Add to oat mixture.
Fill greased tins and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mash shrimp with a fork; add other ingredients, using just enough mayonnaise to create a spreadable consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: marian kempin's layered lettuce plus salad
directions: Place
lettuce	in
9 x 13-inch dish.
Place the next 5 items in layers over the lettuce.
Sprinkle on top the sugar, shredded Cheddar
cheese
and
bacon bits.
Cut into squares. Serves 12 to 15.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for best results.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven; cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Add 2 quarts of water and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes or bake in microwave oven.
Peel eggs, chop whites and set aside.
Put mustard, mayonnaise and egg yolks in a bowl.
Mix.
Add hot potatoes and cut in chunks with knife while mixing.
Add egg whites, onion and pepper.
Add salt, if needed.

title: tsimmis (with meat)
directions: In Dutch oven, brown flanken in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion.
Cook until golden.
Peel and slice carrots. Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Add carrots and potatoes to meat and cook on top of stove at medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add prunes.
