Cook another 45 minutes until soft.
Add water or chicken broth as needed.
Stir/mix as needed.

title: crab dip
directions: Warm mushroom soup in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet over medium heat, breaking it up into small pieces. Cook until no longer pink. Drain well.
Add balance of ingredients.
Mix well and simmer until peppers and onions are cooked.
Makes enough to feed a party.
Recipe is very easily reduced and just as good in small quantities.

title: taco tureen(soup)
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve topped with Fritos.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: steak casserole
directions: Roll steaks in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: sweet mustard pickles
directions: Combine ingredients to make brine for 7 to 8 quarts of pickles. Cut pickles into bite size chunks.
Boil brine ingredients; add pickles to brine.
Reheat.
Place in hot jars (have rings and lids hot).

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, margarine, Karo and salt to a boil on full power.
Continue cooking 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing and oil.
Pour over crackers.

title: bruzzalonai
directions: Add enough oil to brown bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Add homemade tomato sauce to crumb mixture; moisten (pasty).
Add peeled hard-boiled eggs.
Place bread crumb and sauce mixture layered over round steak, coating it one-inch.
Roll up.

title: fruit dessert salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water; chill.
When partially set, fold in softened cream cheese, nuts, fruit and cream.
Chill in 1 1/2-quart mold.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bring to boil over high heat:
sugar, syrup and butter.
Put 3 eggs in bowl.
Slowly add mixture to eggs, stirring all the while. Add pecans and vanilla.
Put in 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix and add flour and cornmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and bell pepper and saute until soft. Add crawfish, tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy pasta for the gourmet
directions: Put garlic through press or cut in tiny pieces.
Cook in butter slowly until light brown.
Cook pasta until soft.
Add all ingredients and stir well.
Add freshly ground black pepper on top if you like.
Easy and delicious.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Half of mix makes 2 layers.
Add vanilla to flavor.
To other half add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon cloves, 1/2 teaspoon allspice and 3/4 cup raisins (after rolling them in flour) to make spice layers.
Alternate these 4 layers with filling.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together jello which has been dissolved in hot water, pineapple with juice and pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate until salad jells.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the oil, food coloring and sugar together, then add 3 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, buttermilk, cocoa and soda.
Mix well and bake until done.

title: honey carrots and onions
directions: In a small saucepan, bring carrots, onions and water to a boil.
Cover and cook until carrots are crisp-tender.
Drain.
Put vegetables in a serving dish and keep warm.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts and bake in pan 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on baked crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: overnight vegetables
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, paprika and water.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Stir well and chill 24 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend ingredients together; spread out in a 9-inch spring form pan on bottom and sides.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: cheese and garlic grits casserole
directions: Fold butter, grated cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and garlic into prepared grits.
Beat egg whites to form stiff peaks; fold into grit mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken legs
directions: Kill chicken.
Cut off its head.
Shave chicken's feathers off.
Cut off chicken's legs.
Put legs in oven for 5 minutes at 279°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, about 1 hour.
Tear into pieces when cool enough to touch.
Mix and simmer the enchilada sauce, soup and water for 15 minutes on medium on stove.
Tear the tortillas into 2-inch pieces (any shape will do).
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, layer:
tortillas, chichen, sauce mixture, and cheese. Repeat until dish is full.
Bake 1 hour at 350.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind the first 5 ingredients together.
Sprinkle salt over layers of vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into clean, hot jars.
Cold pack, seal and label.
Makes 6 pint jars.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine
cranberries, raisins, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and
water
in a large saucepan.
Cook 15 minutes until berries pop
and mixture thickens.
Stir in apple, celery and onion. Simmer
minutes
longer
or until thick.
Cool and refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Pierce garlic bud with fork.
Cook onion, celery and garlic in margarine until tender.
Remove garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors and heat through.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Stir in cocoa, flour and salt.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
Cover with boiling water. Let stand 15 minutes.
Strain in colander and pour more boiling water over onions and peppers.
Let stand 10 minutes and then drain.

title: potato romanoff
directions: Boil potatoes with skin until tender; peel and grate.
Combine potatoes with sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese and salt.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: honey chicken wings appetizer
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing into two parts and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Onto sheet of wax paper or paper plate, sift together flour and baking powder. Set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon peel and vanilla. Using an electric mixer, beat until thick and lemon colored, about 3 minutes. Beat in half of the flour mixture.
In another bowl, using clean beaters, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.

Gently fold whites alternately with remaining flour mixture into yolk mixture. Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Fit a pastry bag with a No. 6 plain 1/2-inch wide tube and spoon batter into bag.
Pipe out batter onto sheet forming 16 strips, 3-inches long and 1-inch wide.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Use spatula and immediately remove to wire rack.
Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until sauce is thick (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese.
Place 1/2 of the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture over noodles, then 1/2 Mozzarella cheese over the cottage cheese mixture, then 1/2 meat mixture over the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: party log
directions: Mix well. Form into 2 logs.
Refrigerate, slice and serve. May be frozen.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually. Blend in egg yolk, vanilla, salt and flour. Press into greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Spread while hot with melted chocolate. Sprinkle with nuts. Cool, but cut while warm.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: Can use deer meat in place of ground beef.
Mix all of the ingredients well and then shape into loaves.
Wrap in foil and seal.
Put them in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Then poke holes in the bottom of foil.
Place the loaves in a pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil oil and vinegar together and cool.
Add remaining ingredients in large bowl at least 24 hours before serving. Cover bowl with Saran Wrap or put into Tupperware bowl with lid and put in refrigerator.
Stir frequently.

title: cheesy egg burritos
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Mix eggs and milk; pour into skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs begin to set.
Add Velveeta; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and eggs are set.
Fill tortillas with eggs, lettuce and tomato; roll up.
Serve with salsa.

title: malted milk ball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour and salt that have been sifted together.
Add chopped nuts.
Pinch off dough in small pieces and cover candy, rolling into shape with palm of hands. Place on ungreased baking sheet for 15 minutes in 325° oven or until pale brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat egg whites first and put aside in bowl.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in 315° oven for 45 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.

title: "ajvar" - eggplant relish
directions: Bake eggplants and peppers in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Turn peppers occasionally to prevent blistering. Remove skins and seeds while they are hot.
Chop eggplants and peppers fine.
Add salt, pepper and crushed garlic.
Add lemon juice to taste and as much oil as the vegetables can absorb.
Mix thoroughly; chill for several hours.

title: lemon braised pork chops
directions: Fry chops until brown; drain and mix catsup and soft drink. Pour over chops, then place a lemon slice on each chop.
Cover and let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar, pecans and Ritz crackers and mix well.
Pour into well buttered baking dish.
Bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears into saucepan.
If there is not enough, add water to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling and remove from fire. Dissolve gelatin in hot pear juice.
Mix in pears and softened cream cheese.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and cherries.
Turn into desired mold.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute celery and onion together in butter.
Add hamburger and brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine mixture with remaining ingredients, except cheese, in a large kettle.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours, adding water as needed.
Ladle into bowls and top with grated cheese.

title: sourdough
directions: Takes about a week to make this starter.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add cracker crumbs, pimento, salt and onion with a dash of pepper.
Mix well. Pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Blend in Cool Whip and spread over Jell-O mixture.
Chill well.

title: tuna chowder
directions: In large pot boil cubed potatoes until just tender, drain off half of the water. Add all ingredients, simmer until cheese is melted. If too thick add small amount of milk to desired consistency. Serve with cornbread.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent, not brown. Meanwhile, cook rice in water for 5 minutes on low heat.
Place rice, onions, cheese and half and half, stirred together, in a casserole baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef jerky
directions: Select 1/2 inch thick flank, round steak or venison steak. Trim away all fat; then partially freeze meat until firm.
Slice across the grain in 1/4 to 1/2 inch wide strips.
Place strips in a shallow dish or a heavy plastic bag.
Add soy or teriyaki sauce to cover meat.
If desired, onion or garlic powder or Worcestershire sauce may be added.
Toss to coat each piece. Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Lift meat from marinade. Drain well.
Air dry for 2 hours.
Arrange on fine screen or cake cooling rack (single layer).
Cover and smoke until meat is completely dry.
Store in airtight container.
Serve as a snack or appetizer.
Great for camping!

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High (100%) for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well. Return to microwave and cook 1 minute more on High.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour and spread mixture quickly onto lightly greased (flexible) cookie sheet.
Let cool one half hour. Break into small pieces.

title: easy quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie crust according to directions for filled one crust pie.
In medium bowl, combine milk, eggs, dry mustard and pepper.
Set aside.
Layer meat, cheese, broccoli and onion in pie crust lined pan.
Pour egg mixture over the top. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: no name dessert
directions: Prepare angel food cake.
Use only 1/2 of cake.
Can freeze the other half of cake.
Whip pudding, ice cream and milk together.
Shred cake in a 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Spread mixture over cake.
Add hot water to jello and let thicken.
Add fruit mix with jello.
Spread over pudding mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, then
blend
in
all other ingredients. Bake in a greased and floured
8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes one pan only.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Add cracklings.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 35 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in water about 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Lightly mash with a fork or potato masher and cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Serve hot.

title: california marinade for chicken
directions: Mix, shake and refrigerate.
Beat well before using.
Pour over chicken parts and marinate overnight.
Broil chicken on outdoor grill until done.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Fold in potato chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add zucchini, sliced thin and sliced onion.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, covered.
Cool a little. Puree in blender.
Add 3 cups water and bouillon cubes and salt. Serve hot or cold.
Freezes well.

title: wassail
directions: Note:
The cinnamon, nutmeg and whole cloves can be put in a small bag.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut into small pieces. Whip the cream.
Soften cream cheese and mix with mayonnaise. Add fruit.
Mix all ingredients well. Freeze.
Serve on lettuce.

title: great barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until well blended.
Great with ribs or chicken.
Also good on meat loaf.

title: broiled cheese sandwiches
directions: Spread mayonnaise on bread.
Place a strip of tomato, slice of cheese and strip of bacon on bread.
Place in a broiler or a 350° oven.

title: ranch fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in thick slices.
Mix with onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet.
Add potato mixture and cover.
Fry at medium heat, stirring frequently, for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Roll each ball in this mixture and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool for one minute on cookie sheet.
Move to wire rack. Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: yogurt smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients for 1 minute and pour into glasses. Makes 1 cup.

title: silver cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda three times, then add alternately with buttermilk and flavoring to the creamed mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a moderate oven 350° in three layers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Remove fat from ham and cut into small cubes.
Beat eggs slightly and add ham.
Season as desired with a few drops of Worcestershire sauce or onion juice.
Line 8-inch pie pan with pastry.
Pour in egg and ham mixture.
Put on top crust.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 more minutes or until set.
Serves 4.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Melt cheese over low heat.
Add sausage to cheese.
Chop tomatoes and add.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and add to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples, pecans and coconut with big spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in tube pan.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Mix yeast and water, then mix with buttermilk. Cut Crisco into flour until size of peas.
Add mixture to flour. Roll and bake at 400° until done. Mixture can be stored in refrigerator in Tupperware bowl for 2 to 3 days.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix
sugar
and flour.	Add vinegar and water.	Cook in double boiler
until
thick.
Add butter and salt.
Pour over beets that have been sliced and cooked tender.

title: grandma's cherry surprise cake
directions: Mix oil and 1 cup sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add to liquid and beat.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon for topping.

title: maple meringue chocolate chip bars
directions: Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and press down.
Beat 4 egg whites and add 3/4 cup of brown sugar. Spread over mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Work with a spoon until light the shortening and sugar.
Add the egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine and add the applesauce and soda; mix well.
Add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in the walnuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: cube steak parmigiana
directions: Season cube steaks with salt and pepper; brown both sides in oil.
In skillet, drain fat.
Add sauce and mushrooms.
Top each steak with slice of Mozzarella; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot spaghetti noodles.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot grease until brown.

title: rich pecan pie
directions: Bring syrup, sugar and butter to boil in saucepan on medium heat. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.

title: t. j. miracle soup
directions: Season with dry onion soup mix. Cut vegetables and cover with water in a large pot.
Boil 10 minutes. Cover on low heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Use as a dip for raw carrots, cauliflower, celery and broccoli.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and peel enough sweet potatoes to make 3 cups mashed. Mix with 1/2 stick melted butter, eggs, milk, 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla.
Spray baking dish with Pam and pour mixture in.

title: peanut butter pie(in honor of ora dunkin)
directions: Blend filling, in order given.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400°
oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the beaten eggs with uncooked rolled oats, salt and granulated sugar.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Add Karo syrup last.

title: dutch updallas, texas
directions: In a heavy skillet, fry diced potatoes and diced onions until brown.
(Onions may be omitted)
Stir and turn until tender and brown, turn the fire down and beat eggs in a bowl.
Add to the skillet and fold until dry.
Add salt and pepper, a little grated cheese is nice!

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Use a 3-quart casserole dish and make layer of tortillas, layer of chicken, layer of sauce, then cheese.
Make about 3 combined layers and end with cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil together all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, stirring constantly until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Stir in vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Drop in nuts. Stir until sugar crystallizes.
Spread out on waxed paper to cool.

title: chicken sates and peanut sauce
directions: Soak 32 (7-inch) bamboo skewers in water to cover for 15 minutes.
Cut the chicken lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices. Thread the slices lengthwise onto the skewers and season them with salt and pepper.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together with Marzetti's slaw dressing.

title: yummy coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package instructions. While still warm, poke holes through cake with knife.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut in bowl.
Pour slowly over warm cake allowing it to absorb in the holes.
After cake cools, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle on coconut.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: In 9 x 13 baking dish, place sweet potatoes and then top with apples. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over apples and sweet potatoes. Dot with butter and cover with marshmallows. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pressure cook steak and onion about 15 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
To thicken, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch to 1/2 cup of reserved liquid.
Stir into simmering sauce.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: caramel icing
directions: In an iron fry pan cook 1/4 cup sugar over medium heat until brown.
While browning the sugar, bring to a boil the milk and the remaining sugar.
Cook until it forms a hard ball.
Add margarine and the browned sugar.
Beat until you are ready to spread on cake.
(I usually beat until it is creamy.)
After frosting cake, you can add drained, crushed pineapple to the top.
Then dribble a small amount of caramel over the pineapple.

title: irene's chili recipe
directions: Boil 1/2 or more of the macaroni or spaghetti according to directions on the package.
(It all depends on how much you want in your chili.)

title: bacon and cheese yummies
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: clear spinach and tomato soup
directions: Good tasting and healthy!
Bring broth to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until spinach barely wilts.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crust Oreos.
Save 1/2 cup.
Combine the rest with butter; press into a 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Mix and pour over cookies.
Refrigerate.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk.
Pour on top.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed cookies on top.
Refrigerate.

title: rosemary jelly
directions: Mix well, crush lightly and taste.
Add a little to cottage cheese to gauge the taste with food.
Add more of one or another herb to suit your taste or try the following recipe.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Toss flaked salmon with remaining ingredients, except dressing, in a large serving bowl.
Toss with oil and vinegar dressing and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: picnic ham with pickling spice
directions: Boil potatoes and prepare like regular mashed potatoes (milk, butter, salt and pepper).
Let cool and add little more butter and milk.
Mix 2 eggs (pre-beaten) to mixture and stir.
Add flour a tablespoon at a time until consistency of dough.
Roll into patties and fry in oil that has had a teaspoon of butter added to oil.

title: fried artichoke hearts
directions: Place artichokes, lemon juice and water in a bowl; let sit for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix dry ingredients; add egg, then dip artichokes in batter; fry in oil and top with cheese of your choice (Cheddar, Parmesan, Mozzarella) and broil until cheese has melted.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses, then add dry ingredients that have been sifted together. Add hot water last; beat until smooth.
Bake in greased shallow pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
The batter is soft, but makes a fine cake.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix them together thoroughly with your hands.
Don't give up; they eventually will stick together nicely.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes. Stick toothpicks in balls and serve hot or cold.

title: beef burritos
directions: Prepare ground beef and taco seasoning mix as directed on packet for taco filling.
Heat tortillas until warm and flexible as directed.
Spoon 3 tablespoons of beef filling down center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Fold bottom third of tortilla over filling.
Fold sides in toward center, leaving top open.
Secure with toothpick.
Serve with Azteca picante salsa.

title: clam seasoned pilaf
directions: Saute onions in margarine and olive oil.
Drain clams.	Add water to make 1 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer, covered for about 25 minutes or until rice is done.
Serves 6-8.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: lemon barbecue chicken
directions: Mash
salt
and garlic in bowl.
Add other ingredients. Chill 24 hours.
Salt and pepper chicken and dust lightly with flour. Brown
pieces
of chicken in oil.
Put chicken in dish or
pan and
pour
sauce over.
Cook in oven until chicken is done.
Turn chicken
often
or baste.
Chicken is good served hot or cold. Sauce is good on seafood also.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Dip pieces in melted butter; roll in crumb and spice mixture.
Place skin side up in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour, or until done.
Do not turn.

title: coral garden
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young, and take only such as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere. Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.

This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well-sweetened with smiles, and flavored with kisses to taste.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity. Keep warm with a steady fire of devotion, and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: baby pizzas
directions: Mix and spread on party rye bread.
Cover well with 1/2 teaspoon pizza sauce and grated Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve warm.
Can be made ahead and frozen until needed.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken and debone. Cut into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Dice onion over chicken.
Slice cheese and add over onion. Add crushed Doritos. Blend tomatoes and soups and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with crushed Doritos and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; take out of pan.
Mix egg, vinegar and sugar.
Pour into bacon fat; stir over heat until mixture thickens. Put over lettuce with the bacon.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to the juice to make 1 cup. Heat with marshmallows until they are melted.
Add 1 cup hot water to jello and dissolve.
Chill until partially jelled.
Mix Dream Whip and set aside.
When jello is partially jelled, mix all ingredients, and chill well.

title: bologna
directions: Mix and shape into 3 long rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove wrap.
Bake in pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Whip eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° until firm.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Combine mixture and pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan (no crust).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
The center will still be soft.
Serve either hot or cold.
Good with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: delicious caramels
directions: Combine cream and milk in a large bowl.
In large cooking utensil, put sugar, syrup, salt and 1 pint of cream and milk mixture.
Cook and stir constantly until it reaches soft ball stage.
Add 1 more pint milk cream mixture.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Add nuts.
Set in cool place 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: quick shepherd's pie
directions: Mix
ground chuck with diced onions and seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook
in
skillet	on
medium
heat until meat is done. Add
can
of
mixed vegetables and cook 1 minute.
Pour into casserole
dish
and
add
layer of reconstituted mashed potatoes. Top
with	grated cheese.	Bake in oven (regular or microwave) until
cheese melts fully.	Good reheated the next day.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mill all of the above ingredients, except whipped topping. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in a 9 x 13 inch container and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 5 minutes before serving. Makes 12 large servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place dried beef in bottom of casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Add pepper and place 1/2 slice bacon on each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Wash beans well.
Boil beans for 2 minutes; simmer for approximately 1 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Add green peppers, onion, garlic and olive oil.
Continue cooking for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: crumb pie shell
directions: Mix well; pat firmly into pan. Chill until firm or bake 8 minutes at 375°. Chill.

title: berry delicious syrup
directions: Mash berries well and strain through a jelly bag or use a juicer.
Add water and sugar to a preserving kettle and place over heat, stirring until dissolved.
Bring to a boil, continue stirring until clear and skim.
Let syrup boil again until a soft ball is formed in cold water, then slowly add the fruit juice. Boil again.
Skim, pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: beef stew with red wine
directions: Cover with enough red wine to cover the entire ingredients. Cover and put in oven at 325° for at least 1 hour.
Serve with homemade bread and a good salad.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Crumble up cake and sprinkle in Kahlua.
First layer is chocolate cake.
Second layer is chocolate pudding.
Third layer is Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers.
Sprinkle top with shavings of chocolate.
Use a large, high round bowl, preferably glass, to show it off!

title: chicken a'la can, can
directions: Boil chicken; reserve 1 can broth; cut up chicken and put aside.
Put soups in deep frypan and heat; add broth and let cook a little longer.
Add rice; stir until mixed.
Then cover for 7 minutes at low heat so as to not stick on bottom.
Lift lid and stir; add chicken pieces.
Pour into baking dish and top with onion rings.
Bake at 400 degrees, just until onion rings brown, only a few minutes.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Roll on floured wax paper and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Decorate as you choose.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Spread half of the Cool Whip in a 13 x 9 pan. Place the ice cream sandwiches side by side on top of the Cool Whip. Then spread remaining Cool Whip on top of the sandwiches. Crumble the Butterfingers and spread on top. Freeze for several hours and then enjoy!

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine caramel pieces and flour.
Add apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into crust; top with pecans. Bake in preheated baking sheet for 40 to 45 minutes until crust has browned.
Serve warm topped with ice cream or cooled.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs together; then add buttermilk.
Then add butter and sugar mixture to flour and spices; stir in jam, nuts and raisins. Stir well.
Bake in a buttered and floured tube (angel food) pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, soda, salt and vanilla; add beaten eggs. Sift flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough until firm, to roll out.
Roll a little sugar on top.
Cut out with 3 or 4-inch cookie cutter.
Bake at 425° until brown on a greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Beat eggs and add oil.
Beat again.
Mix dry ingredients. Soak chicken at least 24 hours.

title: low-fat fettucine alfredo
directions: Blend flour and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook for several minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, parsley, black pepper and cheese.
Stir until well blended.
Serve over cooked fettucine.
Top with additional grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yummy sauce for salmon or tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve over grilled salmon or tuna.

title: turkey tortillas
directions: Lightly brown onions in oil.
Add ground turkey and garlic. Cook until turkey is fully cooked.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on meat and stir until well mixed.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix until thoroughly melted.
Place meat mixture on tortilla; add lettuce and tomato.
Roll up and enjoy!

title: green beans frittata
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until almost crisp.
Add drained beans; toss until heated through.
Add parsley.
Combine eggs and cheese and pour over beans.
Cook over low heat until eggs are just set. Sprinkle with additional cheese and put under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and plums; beat well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix
as directed on box in 2 layers.
When cool, slice cake to make 4 layers.
Fill each layer with the filling.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Mix onion soup, 1890 dressing and apricot preserves, stirring until smooth.
Use approximately equal amounts of dressing and preserves, adjusting to your own taste and the quantity of chicken being prepared.
Coat chicken with sauce, layer in pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Delicious served over steaming rice and peas.
